snippet.title: Amber Alert "Brajaean Sledge"
snippet.description:
KANSAS CITY, MO (KCTV) -¬†Police in Kansas City have recovered the vehicle believed to be used in the abduction of a 15-year-old Kansas City girl on Thursday.

Brajean Sledge was abducted from a home in the 2700 block of Elmwood Avenue after a man entered her grandfather's home and shot her 60-year-old¬†grandfather.

An Amber Alert has been issued in both Missouri and Kansas for Sledge.

Police say Sledge's grandfather was¬†taken to an area hospital and is in serious but stable condition.

The suspect, who could be with Sledge, is described as a black male between the ages of 18-20. He should be considered armed and dangerous.¬†

"We believe she is with the shooting suspect and we believe she is also in danger," said Kansas City police officer Jake Becchina. "They were last seen northbound from here in a 2017 KIA forte license plate MB5 G5B."

At about 8 a.m. Friday, officers recovered the suspect vehicle near 112th Street and Bennington Avenue.

Detectives are actively searching the area and are processing the contents of the vehicle.

Sledge was last seen wearing a white V-neck t-shirt and dark pants. Police say she has black hair with a blonde weave.

The suspect is described as a black male in his late teens last seen wearing a gray hoodie.

Neighbors say they heard gunfire in the area and were shocked to find out what happened.

"If I was the parents, I would be worried as well," neighbor Montay McKinney said. "I know it's a tough situation for the family. I send my condolences."

Police delayed making a statewide Amber Alert Thursday because they believed the girl was still in the Kansas City area. They have since expanded their search.

It should be noted that Sledge goes by multiple different names and aliases:

Brajaean Sledge

Brajean Sweeten

Bre-Shawn

Brayshawn

Brajean

Rayshawn

Anyone who sees Sledge or has information about the suspect or their whereabouts is asked to call 911.

snippet.title: Amber Heard shared a ridiculously racist tweet about Housekeepers
snippet.description:
Amber Heard: BLASTED for Racist Tweet About Housekeepers The actress found herself at the center of a controversy related to this pair of problems on Tuesday, after a tweet she wrote in response to the Immigration and Customs Enforcement Agency (ICE) by establishing a path nearby. of your house.

This is what the 32-year-old star wrote shortly after midnight today:

"I just heard that there is an ICE checkpoint in Hollywood, a few blocks from where I live, all better to give their housewives, nannies and landscapers a ride home tonight," said Tweeted Heard.

Her point here, of course, was that many housekeepers, babysitters, and landscapers are undocumented immigrants and that ICE can stop them and deport them.

She's wrong? Probably not, as a kind of extreme generalization.

But we can see why the Tweet caused an uproar, right?

"I can see where you were going but at some point along the way you took a wrong turn, eliminate this sister," wrote one of the social media.

Heard eliminated the publication, but did not apologize for it.

Instead, she simply made the same point in a different way.

"With this crisis of human rights so politicized, it is difficult to make a simple statement without it being used to distract from real problems," he explained, adding:

"It's hard for everyone not to be negatively affected by this issue in any way."

Amber Heard: BLASTED for Racist Tweet About Housekeepers The actress found herself at the center of a controversy related to this pair of problems on Tuesday, after a tweet she wrote in response to the Immigration and Customs Enforcement Agency (ICE) by establishing a path nearby. of your house.

This is what the 32-year-old star wrote shortly after midnight today:

"I just heard that there is an ICE checkpoint in Hollywood, a few blocks from where I live, all better to give their housewives, nannies and landscapers a ride home tonight," said Tweeted Heard.

Her point here, of course, was that many housekeepers, babysitters, and landscapers are undocumented immigrants and that ICE can stop them and deport them.

She's wrong? Probably not, as a kind of extreme generalization.

But we can see why the Tweet caused an uproar, right?

"I can see where you were going but at some point along the way you took a wrong turn, eliminate this sister," wrote one of the social media.

Heard eliminated the publication, but did not apologize for it.

Instead, she simply made the same point in a different way.

"With this crisis of human rights so politicized, it is difficult to make a simple statement without it being used to distract from real problems," he explained, adding:

"It's hard for everyone not to be negatively affected by this issue in any way."

Amber Laura Heard (born April 22, 1986) is an American actress. She made her film debut in 2004 in the sports drama Friday Night Lights. After small roles in North Country and Alpha Dog, Heard played her first leading role in All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006) and appeared in The CW television show Hidden Palms (2007).

Heard's breakthrough came in 2008 with roles in Never Back Down and Pineapple Express. She received the Breakthrough Award at Young Hollywood Awards. Her appearance in films such as The Informers, The Stepfather, Zombieland, and The Joneses brought her further attention. Pictures and director James Wan comes an action-packed adventure that spans the vast, visually breathtaking underwater world of the seven seas, Aquaman, starring Jason Momoa in the title role.  The film reveals the origin story of half-human, half-Atlantean Arthur Curry and takes him on the journey of his lifetime‚Äîone that will not only force him to face who he really is, but to discover if he is worthy of who he was born to be‚Ä¶ a king. Also starring Amber Heard, Patrick Wilson, Nicole Kidman and Willem Dafoe.

snippet.title: Jason Momoa and Amber Heard Shared Stories Behind the Aquaman
snippet.description:
Actor Jason Momoa and actress Amber Heard, stars of the 2018 American superhero film "Aquaman", have shared their stories and thoughts about the movie which premiered in China on December 7. 

The films tells the story of the half-Atlantean, half-human Arthur Curry, the heir to the underwater kingdom of Atlantis, returns to the underwater and leads his people against his half-brother, Orm, who seeks to unite the seven underwater kingdoms against the surface world. Momoa and Heard play king and queen in the kingdom of Atlantis in the new DC Comics blockbuster. 

In the film, audience had the chance to see plenty of shirtless Momoa, the 39-year-old who played Arthur Curry, which means high requirement for an actor's physique. 

In the interview, Momoa said he had quite enjoyed the shooting without a shirt on.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp and Amber Heard
snippet.description:
While they were married, Johnny Depp and Amber Heard seemed like a perfect Hollywood power couple. Beginning February 3, 2015, the high-profile marriage was always the subject of tabloid gossip, just like any other A-list relationship.

When Heard showed up to Los Angeles Superior Court on two occasions in late May 2016 with visible bruises on her face, filing first for a divorce and then for a restraining order, it seemed something had gone very wrong.

snippet.title: Amber Heard wears knitted vest at Cannes Film Festival
snippet.description: She was pictured keeping a low profile in a car with Heidi Klum's ex-boyfriend, art dealer, Vito Schnabel, on Tuesday.¬†And Amber Heard, 32, appeared in high spirits as she headed onto a boat in Cannes at the 71st annual Film Festival on Thursday.She wore a knitted white vest top which was low-cut in design as she made her way down the promenade in 22 degree heat.¬†The number was tucked into a pair of high-waisted baggy trousers as she walked along with her hands tucked into her pockets.¬†   Share this article   Share  Her blonde locks were styled into loose curls as she battled a little wind as she neared the water.¬†And she kindly posed for snaps with fans as she made the most of her day in the sunshine.¬†  The night before, Amber wore a sensational gold knitted dress as she headed out in France, less than a day after being seen out with Vito, 31.¬†The Rum Diaries actress, who last dated entrepreneur Elon Musk and was married to Johnny Depp before that was seen in a car with Vito in New York on Tuesday.The duo appeared deep in conversation while traveling somewhere in an SUV and ducked down out of sight after spotting onlookers.¬†Schnabel dated America's Got Talent star Klum, 44, off and on from 2014 until 2017.¬†Meanwhile, Amber's ex Elon Musk has a new lady in his life.The Tesla founder made things official with musician Grimes as they graced Monday night's Met Gala in NYC.

snippet.title: Amber Heard is seen at JFK airport in New York
snippet.description: She's been busy promoting her role as Mera in the upcoming Aquaman movie.And Amber Heard didn't appear to be slowing down one bit as she was seen arriving at JFK Airport in New York Saturday.The star, 32, flattered her svelte figure in a pair of skinny jeans as she touched down in the Big Apple.This comes just after it was revealed that her ex-beau Elon Musk has moved on with another woman.The Tesla and SpaceX founder is reportedly dating Tyler Haney, who is the founder and CEO of athletic-apparel startup Outdoor Voices.A source told Page Six that Haney and Musk 'have been dating for a few weeks'.If Heard was bothered by the news, she didn't show it.Amber looked very fashionable during her airport outing.She accentuated her slim figure with a braided leather belt.Tying the look together, the Texas-born talent donned a Western hat and a studded purse at her side while wearing pointy patent leather shoes with a single buckle.Further adding to her accessories, the actress put on a copper pendant necklace, silver earrings and round sunglasses.Heard¬†kept her hair down, looking naturally tousled, also keeping her face makeup free.The ex of Johnny Depp also carried a sizable leather purse stuffed with things for the trip.While making her way out of the airport, the Magic Mike XXL actress reached over her head to check her hat before getting into her ride.On Friday the star was in LA, where she attended a benefit for the Syrian American Medical Society.Amber's been dedicated to the plight of Syrian refugees.Her work with the Syrian American Medical Society took her to Zaatari Refugee Camp in Jordan last month, where she spent time with people fleeing violence in their home country.And before that Heard was in Las Vegas promoting her upcoming blockbuster Aquaman, which comes out December 21.This year will also see the release of her film London Fields and the star has three other projects in the pipeline beyond 2018.

snippet.title: JOHNNY DEPP: AMBER HEARD BEAT HERSELF UP AND BLAMED IT ON ME!
snippet.description: When Johnny Depp and Amber Heard got divorced, they both signed a non-disclosure agreement that prevented them from speaking about their relationship publicly. Thanks to a lawsuit Depp recently filed against a British tabloid, however, their short and tumultuous marriage is currently being reexamined in a UK¬†courtroom. Depps lawsuit is in response to the newspapers claim that he was abusive to Heard during their brief time together. In court documents obtained by Radar Online, the actor goes so far as to accuse Heard of pretending that she had been abused in order to damage his reputation. "The claimant was not drunk or high when he arrived. He came with two of his security ‚Äì Mr. Bett (Sean Bett ‚Äì a former detective with the LA Sherriff‚Äôs Department) and Jerry Judge to collect some of his belongings from Penthouse 3," reads one such document. ‚ÄúThe claimant brought his security guards with him precisely because he was concerned about what Ms. Heard might do. "The phone did not hit Ms..Heard on the face or elsewhere. Nor did the claimant pull Ms. Heard‚Äôs hair or strike her, or grab her face, or touch her. " The filing goes on to allege that Heard pretended to have been assaulted by Depp, seemingly for the benefit of the person she was on the phone with. ‚ÄúUpon hearing Ms. Heard shouting, the security guards immediately, i. within one or two seconds, opened the doors and rushed into penthouse 3 via the kitchen where the claimant was standing," it reads. "Immediately upon opening the door, the security guards observed the claimant standing in the kitchen area, far away from Ms. Heard. "At that moment, Ms. Heard yelled ‚ÄòStop hitting me Johnny‚Äô into the phone. "The claimant was not hitting Ms. Heard, who was standing about 25 feet away from the claimant. ," the document continues. ‚ÄúMs. Heard was visibly shocked to see the security guards enters, and attempted to feign crying. "Ms..Heard changed from the present tense to the past tense and said, ‚ÄòHe hit me with a phone‚Äô, and, ‚ÄòThat‚Äôs the last time you hit me,¬†Johnny. ‚Äô Obviously, the explicit allegations here are quite serious, but the implications might be even more disturbing. Heard was photographed with a black eye in the wake of the incident, which took place just days after Depps mother passed away. So is Depps legal team suggesting that Heard gave herself a black eye in order to frame the actor the same week that his mother died? Clearly, this situation has devolved into a sort of he said-she said tangle that makes it virtually impossible to litigate -- except, of course, the court of public opinion. Perhaps at this point, theres nothing more to do but be relieved that no one was injured more seriously -- and that these two are no longer together..

 In an Instagram photo, the actor has a red anarchy symbol inked over the 'U,' so it now reads 'SCAM.'  Jul 11, 2018  ¬†AceShowbiz -   Johnny Depp has amended a knuckle tattoo he originally had inked in honour of his former wife Amber Heard.  The "Pirates of the Caribbean" star initially had the word "SLIM", his nickname for Amber, tattooed across his right hand after their 2015 wedding, but months after their bitter split in 2016, he had the skin art altered to read "SCUM".  Now it seems Johnny has chosen to update the piece once more.  His Hollywood Vampires bandmate Tommy Henriksen recently shared a photo of Depp's latest tattoo change online, revealing he's had a red anarchy symbol inked over the "U", so it now reads "SCAM".  Johnny has yet to comment on the reason for his tattoo change, but he separated from actress Amber in May, 2016, when she accused him of domestic abuse. They settled the nasty divorce last year.  ¬†The blazing row that finally sent Johnny Depp and Amber Heard‚Äôs ¬≠marriage down the pan was over a pile of poo found in their bed. ¬†Depp accused his wife and her pals of deliberately soiling the sheets after a violent row ‚Äì sparked by him arriving two hours late to her 30th birthday party in April 2016. ¬†She says the excrement was left by Yorkshire terrier Boo, who has bowel problems. ¬†Johnny had stormed out of the LA penthouse during the argument and a housekeeper found the soiled sheets the next day. ¬†The worker suggested the faeces were too big to be from their dog.   ¬†A source close to Johnny, 55, said he thinks there is ‚Äústrong, photographic evidence that connected Amber to the faeces‚Äù and it was left as a ‚Äúprank‚Äù. ¬† But a representative for the actress said: ‚ÄúBoo has some serious bowel  control issues.  ¬†‚ÄúThere was never a joke, it wasn‚Äôt something done to be disrespectful. ¬†‚ÄúIt was an innocent thing, it‚Äôs what pets will do. We don‚Äôt have anything else to say. Ms Heard is moving on and we do not want to engage in this nonsense.‚Äù ¬†Heard, 32, hinted at the bizarre row when she filed for divorce. She got a temporary restraining order, claiming Depp made ‚Äúparanoid and irrational accusations about some delusional idea‚Äù. ¬†She alleged that during the row: ‚ÄúHe began obsessing about something untrue and his demeanour changed dramatically. He became angry.‚Äù  ¬†A month later, in May 2016, the couple had another row about the poo. It was during this that Amber alleges Johnny threw her mobile phone at her, hitting her in the face. ¬†Two policemen who attended the scene have since claimed in legal papers there were no marks on her face. Heard withdrew the request for a restraining order when their divorce was settled. ¬†Depp denies domestic violence. A representative did not respond to requests for comment. ¬†The couple‚Äôs dogs, Pistol and Boo, hit headlines in 2016 when they were smuggled into Australia while Depp was shooting the fifth Pirates of the Caribbean film there. ¬†He and Heard filmed a bizarre apology. ¬†She got custody of both dogs when their divorce was settled in January 2017.

snippet.title: Amber Heard wears knitted vest at Cannes Film Festival
snippet.description: She was pictured keeping a low profile in a car with Heidi Klum's ex-boyfriend, art dealer, Vito Schnabel, on Tuesday.  And Amber Heard, 32, appeared in high spirits as she headed onto a boat in Cannes at the 71st annual Film Festival on Thursday.  She wore a knitted white vest top which was low-cut in design as she made her way down the promenade in 22 degree heat.  The number was tucked into a pair of high-waisted baggy trousers as she walked along with her hands tucked into her pockets.  Her blonde locks were styled into loose curls as she battled a little wind as she neared the water.  And she kindly posed for snaps with fans as she made the most of her day in the sunshine.  The night before, Amber wore a sensational gold knitted dress as she headed out in France, less than a day after being seen out with Vito, 31.  The Rum Diaries actress, who last dated entrepreneur Elon Musk and was married to Johnny Depp before that was seen in a car with Vito in New York on Tuesday.  The duo appeared deep in conversation while traveling somewhere in an SUV and ducked down out of sight after spotting onlookers.  Schnabel dated America's Got Talent star Klum, 44, off and on from 2014 until 2017.  Meanwhile, Amber's ex Elon Musk has a new lady in his life.  The Tesla founder made things official with musician Grimes as they graced Monday night's Met Gala in NYC.

snippet.title: Jason Momoa and Amber Heard launch the latest movie in the DC Universe, 'Aquaman'
snippet.description:
(25 Apr 2018) JASON MOMOA AND AMBER HEARD LAUNCH THE LATEST MOVIE IN THE DC UNIVERSE, 'AQUAMAN'
Jason Momoa and Amber Heard made a splash at CinemaCon in Las Vegas Tuesday (24 APRIL 2018), where they launched the latest DC Universe superhero movie, "Aquaman."
Joining director James Wan at the event, the actors teased the first footage from the upcoming Warner Bros. stand-alone and spoke about their experiences shooting the film. 
Momoa ‚Äì known to fans of TV's "Game of Thrones" as hunky warlord Khal Drogo ‚Äì said he could identify with Arthur Curry/Aquaman's origins.
"Obviously being a Pacific Islander half that, you know, being part Atlantean/part human is something I can identify with," he said.
The star added that "it was just really cool to be brown and a brown skinned superhero was kind of neat to me for all the kids who, you know, all around the world who can have that and get to have that. So I think in these times it felt really need that Zack (Snyder) came up with that."
Heard ‚Äì who stars as Mera, a warrior of Atlantis ‚Äì said it was great to play a strong female character.
"She's very much of this moment, which is, you know, people, you know, being fed up with these two-dimensional, passive reactionary female characters," she said. 
"I think we're over that as an audience, as a society and you see the changes happening and Mera is very much a reflection of that demand for change. She's strong, she's empowered, she's cool, she's kickass, she's a warrior Queen and they pretty much pitched it to me that way."
Wan, known for horror movies including "Saw," "The Conjuring" and "Insidious," said making directing "Aquaman" has been an altogether new experience.
"In a lot of ways I feel like I'm making an animated feature here to some degree," he smiled. "I joke that I'm making 'Finding Nemo 3' sometimes but I think it's a really cool way, and I try to find something different about this world that makes it unique and I think it's going to make a really cool looking visual world."
After the subdued response to last year's "Justice League," Warner Bros. will be hoping "Aquaman" swims its way to success when it hits U.S. and U.K. theaters December 21.
CinemaCon at Caesars Palace, Las Vegas, runs 23-26 April.

Amber's Airlines - High Hopes

Game Description:

Fasten your seat belt and take off with Amber Hope in a new airline game!

From the makers of Delicious, Fabulous and Heart's Medicine, comes a brand new time management adventure that will make your heart soar! Meet Amber Hope, aspiring stewardess for Snuggford Airlines. Amber has dreamed of flying to exotic destinations around the world since she was a girl. But before she can join the elite crew of air hostesses, she'll need to pass her exams. That's not going to be easy, and she'll need your help. Amber's life seems wonderful. She shares her apartment with her pet fish, Sushi. She loves her job and dreams of the day she'll be on an airplane, a full-fledged cabin attendant assisting travellers. The possibilities are endless - "the sky is the limit" as they say. But appearances can be deceiving‚Ä¶ Everything is overshadowed by what happened in her childhood and she can't escape her past. Her lingering guilt and fear are holding her back from achieving the very thing she is trying to achieve. When her plane crashes, Amber is forced to face her fears. As you've heard time and again during safety demonstrations, Amber will have to help herself before she can help others. Is she up to the task? Share the highs and lows of Amber's life. Be there for her and help her ascend to the highest heights! 

- Be transported by a truly wonderful story of love and loss 
- Fly through 60 travel-themed levels, and 30 extra challenging levels 
- Explore the world and get a behind-the scenes look at airport life with 6 unique locations 
- Master 18 mini games that cover every aspect of flying ‚Äì from check-in to security checks, suitcases to passports, safety demonstrations to serving passengers 
- Fasten your seatbelt for amazing, all-new cinematics 
- Experience what it's like to be a real flight attendant - the ups and the downs 
- Unfasten" Amber's diary and discover her secret thoughts as you earn game goals 
- Customize Amber's diary by earning diamonds and make it your own with travel stickers and different covers

snippet.title: Episode001 Amber Prosia Interviewing Marina J
snippet.description:
Welcome to Episode #1 of The Parenting Biz Podcast - coming to you every Monday. This week's featured guest is Marina J. 

When Marina J became a single mum in 2001 her light went out. She couldn‚Äôt find anyone to teach her; not just how to turn her life around, but actually how to flourish. 

So she made a decision: She would do it. 

She put herself on her own program and within 6 months her life turned around in a BIG way and her light turned back ON. 

She had what those around her didn‚Äôt: A system that took her out of her old life and into the new. 

Since then she‚Äôs become a #1 best-selling author, a speaker and a life coach - because your happiness is everything! 

She married the love of her life and lives by the beach near Sydney. 

She‚Äôs been interviewed by Channel 9‚Äôs breakfast show, ABC radio, Fox Sports Radio, 2GB radio, Body + Soul, Better Health and Gardens, and more. 

Her motto? Is that you‚Äôre built to heal; because you‚Äôre built to live that life that‚Äôs waiting for you!

This week, the entire interview has been constructed around The Grand Opening Night for the most famous show in town - ‚ÄúIgnite Your Power‚Äù & Marina J is the main character about to hit the stage! 

We went behind stage with Marina, dove into the four acts of the show, had a remarkable encore and sat back and reflected in the dressing room once the show was over. 

Ignite Your Power demonstrates the foundational core of truly diving inwards to make a difference in not only our personal or business lives but most importantly, in our children‚Äôs...

Here are some key points summarised in the four acts:

First Act: Decide What You Don‚Äôt Want
First step in igniting your personal power
Lots of self help saying ‚Äúdon‚Äôt think negative‚Äù = Marina completely DISAGREES.
Pay attention to this natural step or you‚Äôll be worse off in the future
Decipher what‚Äôs right for you AND what‚Äôs wrong for you
Find and write down where your energy drains are
Worship and trust your B.S detector

Second Act: Desire What You Do
Isn‚Äôt that selfish? YES! The best kind of selfish
Start small - example: what do you want for lunch?
Go with your feeling in the here and now - the rest will follow
We‚Äôre all energy...

Third Act: Detox What‚Äôs In Your Way
Focus on emotional detox
What are you more committed to?
The importance of asking more powerful questions
85% of what‚Äôs in our way, lives underneath in our subconscious 
You can talk all you want, but until you go deep - you‚Äôll always be where you are
Real healing = where you won‚Äôt walk out of this year with the same problems you walked into this year with
We all hold 50% masculine & 50% feminine energy and truly NEED both
Most of us, need to raise the feminine to match the already high masculine energy we‚Äôve all been taught

Fourth and Final Act: Self-Love Action
Self Love = It‚Äôs the act of being kind to yourself
How kind are you being on yourself right now?
Your children learn it from you
If you don‚Äôt love yourself, how do you expect your child to love their self?


Looking back and reflecting on your business & life journey, going back to whichever age you choose, what advice would you share with yourself and how old are you?

Marina would go back to her 8 year old self and teach herself to keep some of the energy inwards - to not always give it all away... 

She has always had a great deal of energy, but wasn‚Äôt aware of how to manage it and would tend to give it out rather than keeping some in and replenishing herself. 

So she would actually receive and invest in herself and move forward. 

She simply didn‚Äôt understand how to contain it... 

Eventually she learned to keep some of it inwards for herself to move forward too. 

Final thought: 
What turns you on?
What turns you off?
Begin asking yourself powerful questions and you‚Äôll be surprised of the wisdom that‚Äôs already within you that just wants to be heard. 
If you want to bring out the best in your children, focus on your own healing and that‚Äôs the legacy you want to be passing onto the next generation...

Want to contact the guest? 
Receive Glitter Bombs (enter your details on Marina J‚Äôs Website): https://marinaj.net/ 
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/MarinaJCoaching/ 
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/marinajcoaching/ 
Twitter: https://twitter.com/MarinaJGoddess

BACK IN SUMMER by Nicolai Heidlas Music https://soundcloud.com/nicolai-heidlas

Amber Laura Heard (born April 22, 1986) is an American actress. She made her film debut in 2004 in the sports drama Friday Night Lights. After small roles in North Country and Alpha Dog, Heard played her first leading role in All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006) and appeared in The CW television show Hidden Palms (2007).

Heard's breakthrough came in 2008 with roles in Never Back Down and Pineapple Express. She received the Breakthrough Award at Young Hollywood Awards. Her appearance in films such as The Informers, The Stepfather, Zombieland, and The Joneses brought her further attention. She next starred in John Carpenter's The Ward, alongside Nicolas Cage in Drive Angry, and alongside Johnny Depp in The Rum Diary, for which she won a Spotlight Award at the Hollywood Film Festival. In 2014 she appeared in 3 Days to Kill, and in 2015 in Magic Mike XXL and The Danish Girl. She played Mera in the 2017 superhero film Justice League, which she reprised in Aquaman.

snippet.title: Aquaman sucks: a Deep Dive into DC's Disaster
snippet.description:
Jason Momoa is back as Aquaman in James Wan's new DCEU film, also starring Patrick Wilson, Amber Heard, Yahya Abdul Matteen II, Nicole Kidman, Willem Dafoe, Temeura Morrison and Dolph Lundgren. 
I think it's one of the worst movies of 2018- here's why.

Once home to the most advanced civilization on Earth, the city of Atlantis is now an underwater kingdom ruled by the power-hungry King Orm. With a vast army at his disposal, Orm plans to conquer the remaining oceanic people -- and then the surface world. Standing in his way is Aquaman, Orm's half-human, half-Atlantean brother and true heir to the throne. With help from royal counselor Vulko, Aquaman must retrieve the legendary Trident of Atlan and embrace his destiny as protector of the deep.

snippet.title: Aquaman - Amber Heard
snippet.description:
Amber Laura Heard was born in Austin, Texas, to Patricia Paige Heard (n√©e Parsons), an internet researcher, and David C. Heard (David Clinton Heard), a contractor. She has English, Irish, Scottish, German, and Welsh ancestry.

Heard appeared in the Academy Award-nominated film, L'affaire Josey Aimes (2005), in which she played Charlize Theron's character in flashbacks. Her other early film credits include: Syrup (2013), Hell Driver (2011) 3D, La famille Jones (2009), Never Back Down (2008), Alpha Dog (2006) and Friday Night Lights (2004). On television, Heard starred on The CW drama, Hidden Palms (2007), and had guest starring roles on Showtime's Californication (2007) and CBS's Esprits criminels (2005).

In 2009, Heard starred in the box office hit, Bienvenue √† Zombieland (2009), opposite Woody Harrelson, Bill Murray and Jesse Eisenberg. She also starred in the suspense thriller, Le beau-p√®re (2009), with Sela Ward, Dylan Walsh and Penn Badgley. In 2008, she garnered attention for her role in the comedic hit, D√©lire express (2008), with Seth Rogen and James Franco. Heard received a 2008 Young Hollywood Award for her breakthrough performance in "Pineapple Express".

She appeared in Rhum Express (2011), opposite Johnny Depp, and John Carpenter's The Ward - L'h√¥pital de la terreur (2010), which premiered at the 2010 Toronto Film Festival. She also starred in the independent film, And Soon the Darkness (2010), in which she additionally served as a co-producer.

Heard starred in Paranoia (2013), opposite Harrison Ford, Liam Hemsworth and Gary Oldman. The film was released by "Relativity Media" on August 16, 2013. She also starred in Robert Rodriguez's Machete Kills (2013), which was released by "Open Road Films" on March 4, 2013, and McG's 3 Days to Kill (2014), opposite Kevin Costner and Hailee Steinfeld, which was released in 2014.

Additionally, her film Tous les Gar√ßons aiment Mandy Lane (2006), which premiered at the 2006 Toronto Film Festival, was released by The Weinstein Co. in theaters in the fall of 2013.

Heard resides in Los Angeles, where she is actively involved with Amnesty International. In 2015, she married actor Johnny Depp, and the two divorced in 2017.

A movie I was attached to recast my role,‚Äù the 32-year-old shared. ‚ÄúI had just shot a two-year campaign as the face of a global fashion brand, and the company dropped me.‚Äù   ¬†Heard continued, ‚ÄúQuestions arose as to whether I would be able to keep my role of Mera in the movies¬†Justice League¬†and¬†Aquaman.‚Äù   ¬†Depp, 55, has¬†vehemently denied¬†all abuse allegations, calling the claims ‚Äúsalacious false stories, gossip, misinformation, and lies.‚Äù   ¬†RELATED:¬†Johnny Depp Opens Up About Playing Grindelwald, Says J.K. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Aquaman is an upcoming American superhero film based on the DC Comics character of the same name, distributed by Warner Bros. Pictures. It is intended to be the sixth installment in the DC Extended Universe (DCEU). The film is directed by James Wan, with a screenplay by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick and Will Beall, from a story by Wan, Beall, and Geoff Johns. It stars Jason Momoa as the title character, with Amber Heard, Willem Dafoe, Patrick Wilson, Dolph Lundgren, Yahya Abdul-Mateen II, and Nicole Kidman in supporting roles. It is the third live action theatrical film featuring the title character, following Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice (2016) and Justice League (2017), and will be the first full-length feature film centered around the character. In Aquaman, Arthur Curry, the heir to the underwater kingdom of Atlantis, must step forward to lead his people against his brother, Orm, who seeks to unite the seven kingdoms against the surface world.

Talks of an Aquaman film began in 2004, with several plans falling through over the years. In August 2014, Beall and Kurt Johnstad were hired to write two competing scripts, and the film was officially announced in October 2014. Wan signed on as director in April 2015 and in July 2016 it was announced the film would move forward with Beall's screenplay, although Wan, Johnstad, Johns and Johnson-McGoldrick all performed various rewrites. Much of the main cast was confirmed throughout 2016. Principal photography began in Australia on May 2, 2017. Most of the film shot at Village Roadshow Studios in Gold Coast, Queensland, with production also held in Canada, Italy and Morocco, and wrapped on October 21, 2017.

Aquaman is scheduled to be released in the United States by Warner Bros. Pictures in RealD 3D, Dolby Cinema and IMAX 3D on December 21, 2018.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Arthur Curry is the reluctant ruler of Atlantis and King of the Seven Seas, who finds himself caught between a surface world constantly ravaging the sea and Atlanteans looking to lash out in revolt, but committed to protecting the entire globe.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

snippet.title: 1. Body Dysmorphia: Creating a Healthy Relationship with Food, Chef Amber Caudle
snippet.description:
Food is one of the most abused substances for unhealthy self-soothing. Creating and sustaining a healthy relationship with food involves healing emotional wounds. Watch how one woman recognized her addiction, got to its source and then used food to heal.

‚ñ¨ Contents of this video  ‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨

03:35 - Passion for cooking
04:39 - The messy, healing journey
05:51 - Dealing with health problems
07:08 - Self-love: healing the body with food

‚ñ¨ About Dr. Nadine Macaluso  ‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨‚ñ¨

Dr. Nadine Macaluso is a psychologist and licensed marriage and family therapist in private practice. She received her master‚Äôs in Counseling Psychology and doctorate in Depth Psychology with an emphasis on Somatic Psychotherapy from Pacifica Graduate Institute in California. Her personal and clinical expertise is in attachment trauma, shame, somatic psychotherapy and relationships. Dr. Nae is also the ex-wife to the infamous Wolf of Wall Street, Jordan Belfort, with whom she shares two beautiful children, Carter and Chandler. Nadine has been happily remarried for 20 years; she and her husband John share a blended family of five children and two dogs, splitting their time between New York and Florida.

Amber's Airlines - High Hopes

Game Description:

Fasten your seat belt and take off with Amber Hope in a new airline game!

From the makers of Delicious, Fabulous and Heart's Medicine, comes a brand new time management adventure that will make your heart soar! Meet Amber Hope, aspiring stewardess for Snuggford Airlines. Amber has dreamed of flying to exotic destinations around the world since she was a girl. But before she can join the elite crew of air hostesses, she'll need to pass her exams. That's not going to be easy, and she'll need your help. Amber's life seems wonderful. She shares her apartment with her pet fish, Sushi. She loves her job and dreams of the day she'll be on an airplane, a full-fledged cabin attendant assisting travellers. The possibilities are endless - "the sky is the limit" as they say. But appearances can be deceiving‚Ä¶ Everything is overshadowed by what happened in her childhood and she can't escape her past. Her lingering guilt and fear are holding her back from achieving the very thing she is trying to achieve. When her plane crashes, Amber is forced to face her fears. As you've heard time and again during safety demonstrations, Amber will have to help herself before she can help others. Is she up to the task? Share the highs and lows of Amber's life. Be there for her and help her ascend to the highest heights! 

- Be transported by a truly wonderful story of love and loss 
- Fly through 60 travel-themed levels, and 30 extra challenging levels 
- Explore the world and get a behind-the scenes look at airport life with 6 unique locations 
- Master 18 mini games that cover every aspect of flying ‚Äì from check-in to security checks, suitcases to passports, safety demonstrations to serving passengers 
- Fasten your seatbelt for amazing, all-new cinematics 
- Experience what it's like to be a real flight attendant - the ups and the downs 
- Unfasten" Amber's diary and discover her secret thoughts as you earn game goals

snippet.title: New Aquaman Images Show Black Manta, Nicole Kidman & Patrick Wilson‚Äôs King Orm
snippet.description:
‚ÄòAquaman‚Äô directed by James Wan and starring Jason Momoa, Amber Heard, Nicole Kidman, Patrick Wilson, Yahya Abdul-Mateen II, Willem Dafoe, Dolph Lundgren and Randall Park. Entertainment Weekly released new images from the set of the film and two Aquaman specific covers. The first cover has Momoa looking into camera in a close up dripping wet and the other cover has Amber Heard as Mera, Momoa, and the first look of Nicole Kidman as Queen Atlanna. The magazine also released 7 new images from the movie and from the set. They range from Abdul-Mateen II as Black Manta looking at his helmet to Momoa and Heard on land looking at ruins to a shot of Kidman holding a young version of Arthur Curry as the sun shines behind her to the first look at Patrick Wilson as King Orm about to do battle possibly with Momoa. A trailer was supposedly screened earlier this week at CineEurope that received some raves.

John Rocha and Perri Nemiroff are here to give you their thoughts about these images and if they think the look of them previews an Aquaman film that is more practical effects rather than CGI. They also reveal which of the images stands out the most to them and why. Let us know what you thought about these images in the COMMENTS section below. Remember to LIKE and SHARE this video on your social media and to SUBSCRIBE to Collider.

snippet.localized.title: New Aquaman Images Show Black Manta, Nicole Kidman & Patrick Wilson‚Äôs King Orm
snippet.localized.description:
‚ÄòAquaman‚Äô directed by James Wan and starring Jason Momoa, Amber Heard, Nicole Kidman, Patrick Wilson, Yahya Abdul-Mateen II, Willem Dafoe, Dolph Lundgren and Randall Park. Entertainment Weekly released new images from the set of the film and two Aquaman specific covers. The first cover has Momoa looking into camera in a close up dripping wet and the other cover has Amber Heard as Mera, Momoa, and the first look of Nicole Kidman as Queen Atlanna. The magazine also released 7 new images from the movie and from the set. They range from Abdul-Mateen II as Black Manta looking at his helmet to Momoa and Heard on land looking at ruins to a shot of Kidman holding a young version of Arthur Curry as the sun shines behind her to the first look at Patrick Wilson as King Orm about to do battle possibly with Momoa. A trailer was supposedly screened earlier this week at CineEurope that received some raves.

John Rocha and Perri Nemiroff are here to give you their thoughts about these images and if they think the look of them previews an Aquaman film that is more practical effects rather than CGI. They also reveal which of the images stands out the most to them and why. Let us know what you thought about these images in the COMMENTS section below. snippet.description:
amber heard hot

https://youtu.be/lmTJJRugYrw

Amber Laura Heard (born April 22, 1986) is an American actress. She made her film debut in 2004 in the sports drama Friday Night Lights. After small roles in North Country and Alpha Dog, Heard played her first leading role in All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006) and appeared in The CW television show Hidden Palms (2007).

Heard's breakthrough came in 2008 with roles in Never Back Down and Pineapple Express. She received the Breakthrough Award at Young Hollywood Awards. Her appearance in films such as The Informers, The Stepfather, Zombieland, and The Joneses brought her further attention. She next starred in John Carpenter's The Ward, alongside Nicolas Cage in Drive Angry, and alongside Johnny Depp in The Rum Diary, for which she won a Spotlight Award at the Hollywood Film Festival. In 2014 she appeared in 3 Days to Kill, and in 2015 in Magic Mike XXL and The Danish Girl. She played Mera in the 2017 superhero film Justice League, which she reprised in Aquaman.

snippet.title: Aquaman = Movie Review 2018 = Jason Momoa, Amber Heard, Yahya Abdul-Mateen
snippet.description:
‚ÄúAquaman‚Äù is a 2018 superhero movie about a man of royal blood that was born outside of the borders of his parent's native country. That country is very secluded and has exotic, advanced technology beyond anything in the rest of the modern world is aware of. There are factions within the country that believe a conflict with the outside world is not only inevitable, but their country should rule the because of its biological and technological superiority. The man of royal blood decides to journey to the reclusive nations and challenge for the throne of the kingdom in order to lead its people into a new geopolitical future. 

If that read like the premise of ‚ÄúBlack Panther‚Äù, then you'd be correct. The newest DCEU movie is very similar to multiple super hero and science fantasy films of recent times, and I make references to those similarities throughout this YouTube video. I also offered a grade of B+ (with reluctant bias), which is explained within the presentation. Strap yourselves in. Batten down the hatches. There are some rough waters ahead.

The movie was directed by James Wan. It stars Jason Momoa, Amber Heard, Willem Dafoe, Patrick Wilson, Dolph Lundgren, Yahya Abdul-Mateen II, Nicole Kidman, Temuera Morrison, Randall Park, Graham McTavish, Ludi Lin, Michael Beach, Leigh Whannell, Djimon Hounsou, and Julie Andrews.

snippet.title: Aquaman Spoiler Review
snippet.description:
Aquaman directed by James Wan and starring Jason Momoa, Amber Heard, Nicole Kidman, Patrick Wilson, Willem Dafoe, Temeura Morrison and Dolph Lundgren swims out to sea this holiday season. The film professes to be an action-packed adventure that spans the vast, visually breathtaking underwater world of the seven seas. The film reveals the origin story of half-human, half-Atlantean Arthur Curry and takes him on the journey of his lifetime‚Äîone that will not only force him to face who he really is, but to discover if he is worthy of who he was born to be‚Ä¶a king.

Kristian Harloff, Perri Nemiroff, Denniz Tzeng and Dorian Parks are here to give you their SPOILER filled review of the film. They look at the action, direction, special effects, visuals and storylines of the movie. They let you know what worked for them in the film and what did not. They also let you know if this is part of the new direction for DC. Let us know what you thought of the movie in the Comments section below. snippet.title: Aquaman Tamil - Nathan's Movie Review | James Wan | Jason Momoa | Amber Heard | Future Talks |
snippet.description:
Aquaman is a 2018 American superhero film based on the DC Comics character of the same name, distributed by Warner Bros. Pictures. It is the sixth installment in the DC Extended Universe (DCEU). Directed by James Wan, with a screenplay by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick and Will Beall, from a story by Geoff Johns, Wan, and Beall, it stars Jason Momoa as the title character, with Amber Heard, Willem Dafoe, Patrick Wilson, Dolph Lundgren, Yahya Abdul-Mateen II, and Nicole Kidman in supporting roles. It is the third live-action theatrical film featuring Aquaman, following Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice (2016) and Justice League (2017), and the first full-length feature film centered around the character. In Aquaman, Arthur Curry, the heir to the underwater kingdom of Atlantis, must step forward to lead his people against his half-brother, Orm, who seeks to unite the seven underwater kingdoms against the surface world.

Sebagai selebriti, penampilan dan kebugaran menjadi hal yang paling penting, seperti Amber Heard. Mantan istri Johnny Depp ini mengaku hari-harinya banyak dihabiskan di gym, terutama dalam masa mempersiapkan perannya sebaga Mera, Queen of Atlantis,  dalam film Aquaman.

Namun, kepada Shape, ia mengaku, rutinitas latihan kebugaran merupakan hal yang lebih santai dan organik buat dirinya. ‚ÄúKetika saya tidak fokus mempersiapkan peran untuk sebuah film, saya memiliki kebebasan. Jadwal dan program kebugaran yang saya jalani setiap hari jadi lebih fleksibel karena disesuaikan dengan jadwal kegiatan sehari-hari. Biasanya saya lebih menikmati sesi olahraga karena saya tidak merasa sedang menjalankan sebuah obligasi,‚Äù ujar aktris 31 tahun ini.

Untuk menghilangkan stres, Amber Heard memilih melakukan olahraga lari karena paling mudah dilakukan dan bisa ia lakukan sesuai keinginannya.  ‚ÄúSaya juga menyukai olahraga lari karena membantu saya mengusir stres, menjernihkan pikiran, dan kembali bisa fokus,‚Äù ujarnya. Menurut Amber Heard, sangat penting memilih kegiatan yang bisa menjaga kesehatan dan bisa membuat kita merasa senang.

Walau sudah terbiasa menjalankan latihan kebugaran secara intens, ia tetap menekankan pentingnya menjaga mood dan menjauhkan diri dari perasaan negatif saat berusaha mencapai target kesehatan dan kebugaran.  Bila kita bisa menikmati hidup, maka kita bisa mendapatkan manfaat yang besar untuk kesehatan dari pola makan sehat yang telah kita terapkan dan latihan kebugaran yang sudah kita jalankan. Boleh nih, kita sontek gaya hidup Amber Heard untuk mendapatkan kesehatan yang lebih baik.

snippet.title: AQUAMAN - Amazing Worlds Trailer (2018) Amber Heard, Jason Momoa, Superhero Movie HD
snippet.description:
AQUAMAN - Amazing Worlds Trailer | Amber Heard, Jason Momoa, Superhero Movie (2018)

AQUAMAN in theaters December 21

From Warner Bros. Pictures and director James Wan comes an action-packed adventure that spans the vast, visually breathtaking underwater world of the seven seas, ‚ÄúAquaman,‚Äù starring Jason Momoa in the title role.  The film reveals the origin story of half-human, half-Atlantean Arthur Curry and takes him on the journey of his lifetime‚Äîone that will not only force him to face who he really is, but to discover if he is worthy of who he was born to be‚Ä¶a king.

The film also stars Amber Heard (‚ÄúJustice League,‚Äù ‚ÄúMagic Mike XXL‚Äù) as Mera, a fierce warrior and Aquaman‚Äôs ally throughout his journey; Oscar nominee Willem Dafoe (‚ÄúPlatoon,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpider-Man 2‚Äù) as Vulko, council to the Atlantean throne; Patrick Wilson (‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù films, ‚ÄúWatchmen‚Äù) as Orm/Ocean Master, the present King of Atlantis; Dolph Lundgren (‚ÄúThe Expendables‚Äù films) as Nereus, King of the Atlantean tribe Xebel; Yahya Abdul-Mateen II (Netflix‚Äôs ‚ÄúThe Get Down‚Äù) as the vengeful Black Manta; and Oscar winner Nicole Kidman (‚ÄúThe Hours,‚Äù ‚ÄúLion‚Äù) as Arthur‚Äôs mom, Atlanna; as well as Ludi Lin (‚ÄúPower Rangers‚Äù) as Captain Murk, Atlantean Commando; and Temuera Morrison (‚ÄúStar Wars: Episode II ‚Äì Attack of the Clones,‚Äù ‚ÄúGreen Lantern‚Äù) as Arthur‚Äôs dad, Tom Curry.

Wan directs from a screenplay by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick (‚ÄúThe Conjuring 2‚Äù) and Will Beall (‚ÄúGangster Squad,‚Äù TV‚Äôs ‚ÄúTraining Day‚Äù), story by Geoff Johns & James Wan and Will Beall, based on characters from DC, Aquaman created by Paul Norris and Mort Weisinger.  The film is produced by Peter Safran and Rob Cowan, with Deborah Snyder, Zack Snyder, Jon Berg, Geoff Johns and Walter Hamada serving as executive producers.

Wan‚Äôs team behind the scenes includes such frequent collaborators as Oscar-nominated director of photography Don Burgess (‚ÄúThe Conjuring 2,‚Äù ‚ÄúForrest Gump‚Äù), his five-time editor Kirk Morri (‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù films, ‚ÄúFurious 7,‚Äù the ‚ÄúInsidious‚Äù films), and production designer Bill Brzeski (‚ÄúFurious 7‚Äù).  They are joined by costume designer Kym Barrett (‚ÄúThe Matrix‚Äù trilogy, ‚ÄúThe Amazing Spider-Man‚Äù) and composer Rupert Gregson-Williams (‚ÄúWonder Woman‚Äù).

snippet.title: Amber Heard, NCT 127, Shawn Mendes, Khalid and more arrive to American Music Awards
snippet.description:
(10 Oct 2018) AMBER HEARD, NCT 127, SHAWN MENDES, KHALID AND MORE ARRIVE TO AMERICAN MUSIC AWARDS
At the American Music Awards, K-pop band NCT 127 made their red carpet debut with all ten members sporting black tuxedos.
Actress Amber Heard also wore black, but with gold embellishments. Her Ralph and Russo gown had a plunging neckline and a thigh-high slit. 
Tyra Banks wore a black military-style hat paired with a playful, shimmering ruby skirt, while Vanessa Hudgens appealed to a softer palette in a baby pink silk gown.
Newcomer Ella Mai wore a mint double-breasted custom Sergio Hudson suit with wideleg pants.
Also on the carpet was Khalid, Shawn Mendes, Dua Lipa and Thomas Rhett.

snippet.title: 'Glee' Cast Reunites! See Amber Riley, Matthew Morrison & More | News Flash | Entertainment Weekly
snippet.description:
On Thursday, Matthew Morrison, otherwise known as the beloved Mr. Schue, shared a photo with some of the cast and crew from Glee, who reunited for dinner in Los Angeles. Breaking bread with Morrison were Jane Lynch (Sue Sylvester), Naya Rivera (Santana), Heather Morris (Brittany), Amber Riley (Mercedes), Chris Colfer (Kurt), Kevin McHale (Artie), Jenna Ushkowitz (Tina), Becca Tobin (Kitty), and Vanessa Lengies (Sugar), plus choreographer Zachary Woodlee, script coordinator Aristotle Kousakis, and writers Matt Hodgson and Michael Hitchcock. Morrison‚Äôs wife Renee Morrison was also in attendance, along with their new baby, 4-month old Revel James Makai.

snippet.title: Jason Momoa and Amber Heard show off their bodies in new Aquaman pics
snippet.description: He's played the role twice before, in supporting roles for Justice League and Batman V Superman: Dawn Of Justice.And Jason Momoa is getting close to his first starring turn as Aquaman, when the movie hits theaters on December 21.The 38-year-old actor showed off his impressive physique on the cover of this month's Entertainment Weekly, along with co-stars Amber Heard, 32, and Nicole Kidman, 50.In the brand new stills, the Game Of Thrones star showcased his bulging biceps and chiseled chest as he struts around shirtless.New ink had been added to the actor's existing tattoos and his wavy long tresses were damp.  Also pictured in form-fitting attire was Amber Heard, who wore a green bodysuit that showed off the starlet's enviable curves.The low-cut garment also showed off the impressive assets of Johnny Depp's ex wife.¬†  The new EW issue features interviews with cast and crew from the DC superhero film, including director James Wan.The Australian filmmaker said: 'The water world my movie takes place in is so separate and so far apart from previous DC movies it‚Äôs like I‚Äôm making my own sci-fi fantasy film.''This is a whole new underwater world nobody has seen before in live action.'¬†  Executive producer Peter Safran also spoke to the publication.He added: 'Rarely has a superhero character been married to the real-life actor as much as Aquaman and Jason Momoa.'¬†'He‚Äôs authentically from two worlds, he‚Äôs this real physical specimen, he‚Äôs got this humor which he‚Äôs never been allowed to play before ‚Äî in every regard he is Aquaman.'In the Warner Bros. film, Heard will play Mera, while Academy Award winning actress Kidman plays Queen Atlanna.

snippet.title: Charlize Theron, Amber Heard, Anna Kendrick celebrate 'incredible women' at charity gala
snippet.description:
(10 Oct 2018) THERON, HEARD, KENDRICK AMONG THOSE CELEBRATING 'INCREDIBLE WOMEN' IN LOS ANGELES
Big names were multi-tasking Tuesday night (9 OCT. 2018) in downtown Los Angeles.¬†¬†
Charlize Theron, Amber Heard and Kate Beckinsale were among those attending the Porter's Third Annual Incredible Women Gala, paying tribute to the fashion magazine's celebration of women who have changed the global conversation over the past year.
Ironically, most attendees were not there to speak - at least with the press - as they simply showed off their haute couture to photographers, and zipped into the venue without a word.
The event took place the night of the American Music Awards, which many had attended, so some likely were talked out.
But others were happy to discuss this year's "Incredible" theme: "One Year Stronger," referring to successes achieved in the year since the #MeToo and Time's Up movements emerged after allegations of sexual abuse by film exec Harvey Weinstein, and opened discussion of not only abuse but also pay disparity, glass ceilings and lack of job opportunities for women in Hollywood. 
It wasn't long after that the movements moved out of Hollywood and began to address those matters facing women in all businesses, all over the world.
Actress Ellen Pompeo, star of creator Shonda Rhimes "Grey's Anatomy" observed, "I think that Shondaland has always sort of operated in the same way.¬†¬†But I think with respect to the rest of the entertainment community, we've certainly seen film and television, outside of Shondaland, cast differently.¬†¬†And I think now we have started the conversation about behind the scenes and below the line, and the crews that staff these shows and staff these movies.¬†¬†We still have a long way to go.¬†¬†But I think at least the conversation has been started - that now below the line and behind the scenes, the crews have to start looking more like the real world." 
Recording artist Annie Lennox said she was lucky never to have to deal with the pay disparity issues, as she and Eurythmics' bandmate Dave Stewart split proceeds evenly.¬†¬†But she acknowledged she's among the few women who have been in that scenario, and called the #MeToo movement "incredible."
"I think what's happened is one of the positives we can take from it is open dialogue, when we just didn't have any dialogue.¬†¬†This, this, these things have been going on forever.¬†¬†And now, it's out; it's out of the bag.¬†¬†The genie is out of the bottle.¬†¬†And so the dialogue has begun.¬†¬†And my focus of interest is in global feminism.¬†¬†I'm interested in young girls and women living in absolutely intolerable, oppressive circumstances, who don't have a hope, you know, for their future, who don't get access to the things we take for granted.¬†¬†So my focus has been on the world, you know.¬†¬†So I call myself a global feminist.¬†¬†And the #MeToo movement is incredible . And all of this is supportive, in terms of my activism and my advocacy as a global feminist." 
Director Catherine Hardwicke couldn't find a job after directing the first, blockbusting "Twilight" film entry, and it's taken her a decade to regular land big movies again.
But while she's regularly complained about that situation, she's also done her best to share her continued "Twilight" fame with other female filmmakers.
Actress Minnie Driver, who is the top-billed star of an acclaimed network sitcom, "Speechless," said women have a long way to go.

Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/APArchives ‚Äã‚Äã

snippet.title: Amber Heard wears knitted vest at Cannes Film Festival
snippet.description: She was pictured keeping a low profile in a car with Heidi Klum's ex-boyfriend, art dealer, Vito Schnabel, on Tuesday.¬†And Amber Heard, 32, appeared in high spirits as she headed onto a boat in Cannes at the 71st annual Film Festival on Thursday.She wore a knitted white vest top which was low-cut in design as she made her way down the promenade in 22 degree heat.¬†The number was tucked into a pair of high-waisted baggy trousers as she walked along with her hands tucked into her pockets.¬†   Share this article   Share  Her blonde locks were styled into loose curls as she battled a little wind as she neared the water.¬†And she kindly posed for snaps with fans as she made the most of her day in the sunshine.¬†The night before, Amber wore a sensational gold knitted dress as she headed out in France, less than a day after being seen out with Vito, 31.¬†The Rum Diaries actress, who last dated entrepreneur Elon Musk and was married to Johnny Depp before that was seen in a car with Vito in New York on Tuesday.The duo appeared deep in conversation while traveling somewhere in an SUV and ducked down out of sight after spotting onlookers.¬†Schnabel dated America's Got Talent star Klum, 44, off and on from 2014 until 2017.¬†Meanwhile, Amber's ex Elon Musk has a new lady in his life.The Tesla founder made things official with musician Grimes as they graced Monday night's Met Gala in NYC.

snippet.title: Jason Momoa, Amber Heard, Willem Dafoe in Aquaman Extended Trailer #2 (2018)
snippet.description:
Your comments and likes are truly appreciated...please consider subscribing
Thank you



Aquaman is an upcoming American superhero film based on the DC Comics character of the same name, distributed by Warner Bros. Pictures. It is the sixth installment in the DC Extended Universe (DCEU). Directed by James Wan, with a screenplay by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick and Will Beall, from a story by Geoff Johns, Wan and Beall, it stars Jason Momoa as the title character, with Amber Heard, Willem Dafoe, Patrick Wilson, Dolph Lundgren, Yahya Abdul-Mateen II, and Nicole Kidman in supporting roles. It will be the third live action theatrical film featuring the title character, following Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice (2016) and Justice League (2017) and the first full-length feature film centered around the character. In Aquaman, Arthur Curry, the heir to the underwater kingdom of Atlantis, must step forward to lead his people against his brother, Orm, who seeks to unite the seven kingdoms against the surface world.

snippet.title: Weam, a SAMS Thalassemia patient in Jordan
snippet.description:
During our mission to Jordan with SAMS Goodwill Ambassador Amber Heard this April, we met 12-year-old Weam. Weam is a dialysis patient who suffers from a life-threatening condition called thalassemia. She and 12 other children living in Jordan‚Äôs al-Zaatari Refugee Camp have not received needed treatments due to high costs and budget cuts earlier this  year. We followed up with Weam in July to check on her progress and her hopes for the future.

To learn more and support Weam and other youth with Thalassemia in Zaatari Camp, visit Amber Heard's Crowdrise campaign here:

snippet.title: Amber Heard accepts the award for 'Woman of the Year' during the GQ ceremony (November 15, 2017)
snippet.description:
Accepting her award in Sydney - which Heard joked was ‚Äúon behalf of my dogs?‚Äù - the actress spoke out about her sexuality, and how the marriage equality vote has impacted her personally.
‚ÄúI feel really honoured to be in this room tonight with examples of real gentlemen, it's a rare thig these days, and I feel honoured. ‚ÄúI also think the timing is amazing today: I flew in from Los Angeles after being here for eight months shooting, I thought I had finally escaped...but no. Two days later I flew back to accept this award...I'm assuming on behalf of my dogs Pistal and Boo. Well ufortunately they could not make it tonight.

‚ÄúI was on the plane [to Sydney on Wednesday morning] and we were landing and the pilot came on the speaker and said, "Welcome to Sydney... and by the way, we just got news that the vote came in‚Ä¶ and the majority of Australians support the right for all Australians to marry the person they love." And I thought this is a commercial airline, and the pilot is announcing this news, and wow that's brave. And then something unbelievable happened: the whole plane erupted in this chorus of applause [...] Every single person on the plane clapped,‚Äù she added. 
Remembering a time when being opening gay or lesbian wasn‚Äôt ok, Heard recalls a time she was warned about being involved with another woman - and how it still impacts her to this day. 
‚ÄúI remember ten years ago when I refused to drop my girlfriend‚Äôs hand at the time, everyone told me that was a death sentence in Hollywood. Ten years late the whole plane is clapping at this offhanded news announcement that the pilot decided to make, and it brought chills to my body and a tear to my eye - and here I am.‚Äù

‚ÄúSo I feel really lucky to be here today, and I feel really honoured and humbled. And I appreciate it very much.‚Äù
@GQ Australia

snippet.title: Amber Heard Faces Backlash for Tweet About ICE Checkpoints
snippet.description:
Amber Heard Faces Backlash for Tweet About ICE Checkpoints:
http://www.instyle.com/news/amber-heard-backlash-ice-tweet.

Thanks for watching, subscribe for more videos:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCStnChYQHsa2Uhl-y121BdQ?sub_confirmation=1
¬†In an effort to take a stand against Donald Trump's "zero tolerance" immigration policy,¬†tweeted a message that many followers have called out as racist.   ¬†Early Tuesday morning, Heard posted¬†about an ICE checkpoint near her L.A. home, writing, ‚ÄúJust heard there‚Äôs an ICE checkpoint in Hollywood, a few blocks from where I live.¬†Everyone better give their housekeepers, nannies and landscapers a ride home tonight‚Ä¶‚Äù The tweet has since been deleted.   ¬†The issue? The message¬†played into the stereotype that service-workers, such as housekeepers, nannies, and landscapers, would need to worry about an ICE checkpoint because of their legal status,¬†reinforcing the idea that all or most people who hold such jobs arrived in the country illegally. Some followers also accused the actress of relegating all¬†immigrants to the roles of "the help."¬†  ¬†She continued, ‚ÄúCheckpoints on your home streets‚Ä¶. Is this the ‚Äògreat‚Äô America we‚Äôre aiming for? Followers swiftly called on her to reconsider her comments. They explained that even if she meant the message to come across as a¬†tad satirical‚Äîmeaning to drag her neighbors for living lives of excess with hired help‚Äîthe post ultimately comes across¬†as racist and aloof.   ¬†Following the backlash, Heard took down¬†the original tweet and posted a new message lamenting¬†that "it is hard to make a simple statement w/out it being used to distract from the real issues."¬†  ¬†Though her original message was muddled on Twitter, Heard's recent political activism points to just a poor choice of words this time.¬†On Instagram, the 32-year-old¬†has highlighted a variety of organization working to further¬†women‚Äôs reproductive rights, plus the work of the United Nations Human Rights Council. She also recently headed to Texas to protest President Trump‚Äôs immigration policy, and promoted the Families Belong Together rallies against it.   ¬†Judging by Heard's¬†recent posts,¬†it's easier to give her the benefit of the doubt. snippet.title: Amber Heard, Patrick Wilson & James Wan talk Aquaman
snippet.description:
Amber Heard, Patrick Wilson and Director James Wan are interviewed for their movie Aquaman, the latest in the DC / Justice League franchise.

Patrick Wilson argues that his character looks more like Legolas than Eminem, working with James Wan again.

Amber Heard talks about the joy of not being a reactionary damsel in distress, and how the hyper-sexualisation of women does not accurately define most women.

James Wan talks about walking the fine line between the colourful comic book and the serious environmental and family-themed  elements at play. 

Arthur Curry learns that he is the heir to the underwater kingdom of Atlantis, and must step forward to lead his people and be a hero to the world.

snippet.title: El Poder de la Mujer en Aquaman con Amber Heard.
snippet.description:
EL PODER DE LA MUJER ES GRANDE ESPECIALMENTE PARA NUESTRAS HIJAS, UN MENSAJE QUE QUIERE DAR LE AMBER A TODAS LAS MUCHACHAS. 

AMBER ES EXCELLENTE EN ESTA PELICULA AQUAMAN QUE ESTRENA HOY EN CINES. 
Once home to the most advanced civilization on Earth, the city of Atlantis is now an underwater kingdom ruled by the power-hungry King Orm. With a vast army at his disposal, Orm plans to conquer the remaining oceanic people -- and then the surface world. Standing in his way is Aquaman, Orm's half-human, half-Atlantean brother and true heir to the throne. With help from royal counselor Vulko, Aquaman must retrieve the legendary Trident of Atlan and embrace his destiny as protector of the deep.

Amber Heard sips wine as she enjoys a sunny outdoor lunch with pal... after making donation to children‚Äôs hospital

snippet.title: Amber Heard looks chic in sequinned blazer and fedora hat
snippet.description: She will grace cinema screens as Mera in upcoming action flick Aquaman.And Amber Heard looked undeniably chic as she took to the red carpet at the Warner Bros presentation at CinemaCon 2018¬†in Las Vegas on Tuesday  to represent the film.The talented actress, who turned 32 on Sunday, showed off her sartorial flair in a tight white vest top paired with a glittering black blazer, studded with silver sequins.Showing off her slender legs, The Rum Diary star slipped into a pair of black high-waisted jeans and added height to her toned frame with black stiletto heels.The blonde beauty added a stylish edge with a black fedora hat.  Her caramel tresses were styled in bouncy waves, parted on the side while her stunning features were accentuated with feline flicks of liner, gold shadow and a slick of red lipstick.Flashing a radiant smile, the star looked happier than ever as she posed up with cast members from the film including hunky Jason Momoa, 38 who plays the titular role.  Handsome Jason, who recently wed long-term partner Lisa Bonet, showed off his muscular frame in a black t-shirt, navy blazer and leather trousers, while his flowing chestnut locks were worn down, over his shoulders.¬†Warner Bros unveiled rough footage from the film at CinemaCon, with the flick due to be released on December 21 this year.¬†The DC Comics adaptation will see Aquaman (Jason Momoa) battling his evil half-brother¬†(Patrick Wilson) after returning to the Kingdom of Atlantis.¬†He is also trying to prevent an imminent conflict between sea dwellers and those living on the 'surface world.'¬†¬†¬†¬†Heard was out after the Children‚Äôs Hospital Los Angeles named her on a list of donors who pledged between $1,000,000 and $4,999,999, squaring with her previous vow to forward the $7 million divorce settlement she got from Johnny Depp to charity.¬†The Zombieland beauty had told previously told¬†People¬†that her 'philanthropic efforts have always been centred around medical care, especially with women and children.¬†  'Medical care always struck me as a basic human right and necessity. I have been doing this type of work for the last 14 years with children‚Äôs hospitals and bringing, hopefully, laughs and alleviation and distraction to kids that are severely ill,' said Heard, as the two-year anniversary of her May 2016 divorce filing with Depp approaches.After the celebrity pair, who initially got together on the set of 2011's The Rum Diary, finalized the details of their split in August of 2016, Heard said that she was forwarding the American Civil Liberties Union half of the $7 million total.¬†¬†¬†She said the monies were forwarded 'with a particular focus to stop violence against women,' amid the allegations of verbal and physical abuse she aimed at Depp in their split.¬†   The actress, who shares the screen with Cara Delevingne in the upcoming crime drama London Fields, issued a statement following the settlement stressing that finances played no role in the show business split.She said, 'As describe

snippet.title: Aquaman Official Extended Trailer (2018) | Jason Momoa, Amber Heard, Willem Dafoe
snippet.description:
Aquaman is the king of all things aqua. He can breathe underwater, swim at tremendous speeds, and telepathically communicate with sea life. Being able to withstand ocean depths, he gets bonus points on land with his superhuman strength, enhanced senses, and nearly impenetrable skin.

Aquaman releases in theaters December 21.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Debunks Johnny Depp's Claim She Hit Him 'Twice in the Face'
snippet.description:
Amber Heard Debunks Johnny Depp's Claim She Hit Him 'Twice in the Face':
https://www.aceshowbiz.com/news/view/00124006.html.

Thanks for watching, subscribe for more videos:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCtZxDBnmqFO79Gho7odw-Dg?sub_confirmation=1
 The 'Aquaman' actress denies the allegations made by her ex-husband in court documents, which the actor filed as part of his libel lawsuit against The Sun.  Aug 2, 2018  ¬†AceShowbiz -  An attorney for Amber Heard has denied claims she hit her ex-husband Johnny Depp twice in the face for being late to a party.   The allegation emerged as part of the Hollywood actor's libel lawsuit against British newspaper The Sun, who he is suing for running a story in April which claimed he is a "wife-beater" and criticised his casting in Harry Potter spin-off Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald. ¬†   In court documents obtained by British publication The Mirror, the star's legal team claimed that Amber became upset after her then-husband turned up two hours late to her birthday party in April 2016, and went on to become "aggressive and violent" after guests left, "punching him twice in the face". His lawyers also claimed that the actress had been drinking and had to be pushed away by the Pirates of the Caribbean star to stop the alleged abuse.   "These allegations are totally false," Amber's attorney told The Mirror. "One needs only read the recent Rolling Stone article about Mr Depp and the lawsuit filed against him by a location manager, among many other recent news stories and lawsuits, to understand his state of mind."   Her attorney was referring to a recent interview the 55-year-old gave to the music magazine where he detailed his drinking, depression and dwindling fortune, and claims by location manager Gregg 'Rocky' Brooks that Johnny became violent after he informed the actor that he only had one more chance to shoot a scene in Los Angeles in April 2017.   Amber and Johnny, who met while filming The Rum Diary together in 2011, finalised their divorce in January 2017 after a two-year marriage.  The 'Aquaman' actress denies the allegations made by her ex-husband in court documents, which the actor filed as part of his libel lawsuit against The Sun.  Aug 2, 2018  ¬†AceShowbiz -  An attorney for Amber Heard has denied claims she hit her ex-husband Johnny Depp twice in the face for being late to a party.   The allegation emerged as part of the Hollywood actor's libel lawsuit against British newspaper The Sun, who he is suing for running a story in April which claimed he is a "wife-beater" and criticised his casting in Harry Potter spin-off Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald. ¬†   In court documents obtained by British publication The Mirror, the star's legal team claimed that Amber became upset after her then-husband turned up two hours late to her birthday party in April 2016, and went on to become "aggressive and violent" after guests left, "punching him twice in the face". His lawyers also claimed that the actress had been drinking and had to be pushed away by the Pirates of the Caribbean star to stop the alleged abuse.   "These allegations are totally false," Amber's attorney told The Mirror. "One needs only read the recent Rolling Stone article about Mr Depp and the lawsuit filed against him by a location manager, among many other recent news stories and lawsuits, to understand his state of mind."   Her attorney was referring to a recent interview the 55-year-old gave to the music magazine where he detailed his drinking, depression and dwindling fortune, and claims by location manager Gregg 'Rocky' Brooks that Johnny became violent after he informed the actor that he only had one more chance to shoot a scene in Los Angeles in April 2017.   Amber and Johnny, who met while filming The Rum Diary together in 2011, finalised their divorce in January 2017 after a two-year marriage. snippet.title: Johnny Depp accuses ex-wife Amber Heard of punching him in the face: report
snippet.description: -The troubled actor reportedly filed court documents accusing Heard of assaulting him after an April 2016 dinner party as part of a libel lawsuit against British tabloid The Sun.Depp  55  claimed in the documents that the Aquaman actress violently punched him twice in the face after he showed up two hours late to her 30th birthday dinner  according to People.The Pirates of the Caribbean star reportedly said he was held up by his business manager and accountants prior to the dinner  but that hed let Heard know hed be late  only to find her acting cold when he finally arrived.Depp claimed an allegedly intoxicated Heard became aggressive and violent later in the night as he read in bed  and that he was forced to grab her arms and push her onto the bed in order to stop her from punching him.An attorney for Heard dismissed the allegations as totally false and noted the multiple other assault lawsuits in which Depp is currently embroiled.Mr. Depp is currently being sued in multiple venues  including for assaulting a location manager on the set of City of Lies  the attorney told People. On many occasions  eyewitnesses observed the extent of the abuse Mr. Depp inflicted on Ms. Heard.Heard  32  accused the actor of domestic violence around the same time she filed for divorce in May 2016.She claimed Depp threw an iPhone at her face  and offered up photographic evidence of her bruises when she requested a temporary domestic violence restraining order  which was granted.Depp reportedly disputed her recollection of the nights events in the documents  claiming instead that he tossed the phone onto the couch  and that it never hit Heard.She also alleged that a drunk and high Depp grabbed her hair and shoved her to the floor the night of her 30th birthday dinner.The documents were filed as part of an ongoing libel lawsuit against The Sun  which labeled him a wife-beater in an April article questioning why he still had a role in Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald.Heard and Depp were officially divorced in January 2017 after 15 months of marriage  and she received a $7 million settlement  which she claimed would be donated to charity.

The Texas native is currently dating Heidi Klum's ex-boyfriend, Vito Schnabel, according to Us Weekly. He ended an intermittent relationship with Elon Musk in February 2018. Prior to his relationship with Musk, Heard was married to actor Johnny Depp from 2015-2017.

Variety reported that in May 2016, Tillet Wright, a mutual friend of the couple, called 911 at the actress' request.

Since separating from Depp, Heard has thrown herself into her film career and her charitable work. He is currently defending the cause of a 12-year-old Syrian refugee named Weam.

Amber explained to her millions of followers that the girl "needs a blood transfusion" and that her medical care was expensive. She has partnered with Crowdrise to help pay the girl's medical bills.

3 Days To Kill, il film in onda su Rai 2 oggi, luned√¨ 30 aprile 2018 alle ore 21.20. Una pellicola di genere thriller del 2014 che √® stata diretta da McG, nome d'arte di Joseph McGinty Nichol (Terminator salvation, Charlie's Angels, Una spia non basta) ed interpretata da Amber Heard (Justice League, Never back down - Mai arrendersi, London fields), Kevin Costner (Guardia del corpo, Balla coi lupi, Robin Hood - Principe dei ladri) e Hailee Steinfeld (The dege of seventeen, Pitch perfect 2 e 3, Il Grinta). Soggetto e sceneggiatura sono stati scritti da Luc Besson (Valerian e la citt√† dei mille pianeti, Leon, Il quinto elemento), presente anche nelle vesti di produttore. Secondo le critiche il film soffre di una mancanza di direzione. Da una parte si tratta di un action movie senile, con tutti i luoghi comuni dell'eroe al tramonto e l'ultima missione che dovrebbe salvargli la vita e garantirgli una vecchiaia di pace e serenit√†. D'altra parte il film cerca di contaminare questa base action con la commedia e il melodramma della gestione famigliare e del rapporto fra Ethan e la figlia Zoey, cresciuta praticamente senza un padre e che ora lo vede scomparire, dopo avergli promesso un ultimo periodo insieme, per l'ennesima missione segreta e pericolosa. Ma ecco nel dettaglio la trama del film.

Amber's Airlines - High Hopes

Game Description:

Fasten your seat belt and take off with Amber Hope in a new airline game!

From the makers of Delicious, Fabulous and Heart's Medicine, comes a brand new time management adventure that will make your heart soar! Meet Amber Hope, aspiring stewardess for Snuggford Airlines. Amber has dreamed of flying to exotic destinations around the world since she was a girl. But before she can join the elite crew of air hostesses, she'll need to pass her exams. That's not going to be easy, and she'll need your help. Amber's life seems wonderful. She shares her apartment with her pet fish, Sushi. She loves her job and dreams of the day she'll be on an airplane, a full-fledged cabin attendant assisting travellers. The possibilities are endless - "the sky is the limit" as they say. But appearances can be deceiving‚Ä¶ Everything is overshadowed by what happened in her childhood and she can't escape her past. Her lingering guilt and fear are holding her back from achieving the very thing she is trying to achieve. When her plane crashes, Amber is forced to face her fears. As you've heard time and again during safety demonstrations, Amber will have to help herself before she can help others. Is she up to the task? Share the highs and lows of Amber's life. Be there for her and help her ascend to the highest heights! 

- Be transported by a truly wonderful story of love and loss 
- Fly through 60 travel-themed levels, and 30 extra challenging levels 
- Explore the world and get a behind-the scenes look at airport life with 6 unique locations 
- Master 18 mini games that cover every aspect of flying ‚Äì from check-in to security checks, suitcases to passports, safety demonstrations to serving passengers 
- Fasten your seatbelt for amazing, all-new cinematics 
- Experience what it's like to be a real flight attendant - the ups and the downs 
- Unfasten" Amber's diary and discover her secret thoughts as you earn game goals 
- Customize Amber's diary by earning diamonds and make it your own with travel stickers and different covers
