snippet.title: AMBER HEARD POSTS A SEXY PHOTO ON SOCIAL MEDIA AMID TROPICAL VACATION
snippet.description:
Amber Heard Posts Instagram Picture Showing Off Backside In White Swimsuit The actress is taking a tropical vacation after launching herself in her film career and philanthropic causes.

Amber Heard was seen on vacation wearing a white bathing suit, showing her assets for a portrait taken and posted on her official Instagram. The film star added in the caption: "Sometimes a sign appears" in the photograph where she is seen hugging a palm tree with her hair in two French braids during her tropical vacation.

The Texas native is currently dating Heidi Klum's ex-boyfriend, Vito Schnabel, according to Us Weekly. He ended an intermittent relationship with Elon Musk in February 2018. Prior to his relationship with Musk, Heard was married to actor Johnny Depp from 2015-2017.

That marriage ended with the actress of the Justice League accusing Depp in April 2017 of appearing at his birthday party on April 22 "drunk and drugged." She stated that "she threw me violently to the floor" after grabbing her by the hair, as reported by Variety.

Variety reported that in May 2016, Tillet Wright, a mutual friend of the couple, called 911 at the actress' request. According to Heard, the conversation began very normally, but then Depp "began to obsess about something that was not true and his behavior changed drastically". Heard said: "Johnny grabbed the cell phone, rolled his arm like a baseball pitcher and threw the cell phone, hitting my cheek and my eye with great force," Heard said. "Then he forcibly pulled my hair back while trying to get off the couch ... Johnny kept yelling at me, pulling my hair, hitting me and grabbing me violently in the face."

Since separating from Depp, Heard has thrown herself into her film career and her charitable work. He is currently defending the cause of a 12-year-old Syrian refugee named Weam. "She is currently suffering from a fatal illness and desperately needs our help," the actress said on Instagram.

Amber explained to her millions of followers that the girl "needs a blood transfusion" and that her medical care was expensive. She has partnered with Crowdrise to help pay the girl's medical bills. On the official Heard website, she wrote: "She lives in the Zaatari refugee camp in Jordan and suffers from thalassemia, a genetic blood disorder. The day I met her, her father took her to the SAMS center in Zaatari Camp because she he had fainted and he felt weak. "

"To save his life, he needs blood transfusions every 20 days and iron chelation (oral medications) every day." The cost of this life-long treatment is around $ 900 per month, and his family can not afford it. transfusion from a local NGO, but due to budget cuts, Weam has not been able to receive treatment in the last two months, "Heard said.

So far, Heard's efforts have raised more than $ 10,000 for the cause.

snippet.title: Charlize Theron, Amber Heard arrive to HFPA‚Äôs annual grants banquet, attendees are divided over Osca
snippet.description:
(10 Aug 2018) CHARLIZE THERON, AMBER HEARD ARRIVE TO HFPA'S ANNUAL GRANTS BANQUET, ATTENDEES ARE DIVIDED OVER OSCAR CHANGES
Lena Waithe is all for the new popular film category at the Oscars. 
The actress and Emmy-winning "Master of None" writer is thrilled that the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences is introducing an award for "outstanding achievement in popular film."
"I am all for it because a lot of those popular pictures have people in them that look like me and an Oscar is an Oscar is an Oscar. So people think it's so easy to win a popular Oscar? Do me a favor and go win one. But I think it's important. I think the Oscars have to change because the world is changing, people are changing. And Oscar day is like Christmas at my house. I have so many memories. I can still, you know, (remember) when Tom Hanks won the Oscar for 'Philadelphia.' He talked about the streets of heaven being lined with angels and 'act well the part and there the glory lies.' And Halle Berry winning the award and Whoopie Goldberg hosting that same night when they honored Sidney Poitier and Denzel Washington, all those things. It's an important show. It's sort of our Super Bowl. It represents us. So we have to make sure it's changing with the times because if we don't, then people will stop watching it and that will be horrible. So I'm here for the popular vote! Let's do it," she said. 
Waithe, who attended the Hollywood Foreign Press Association's annual grants banquet Thursday (9 AUG. 2018), was not surprised that Wednesday's announcement proved remarkably unpopular, at least among film critics and some academy members. 
"Look, I mean, the Oscars is an institution and it's like apple pie. So nobody wants to change the recipe for apple pie. But if changing the recipe makes it taste better, then let's do it. I'm here for it, man. I think it's important," Waithe said. 
The introduction of a "popular film" category, beginning with the upcoming Feb. 24 ceremony to be televised by ABC, did not sit well with some. 
"I'm not so happy about that honestly. I think it's a difficult thing for‚Ä¶ We are not the MTV Awards and I found it disappointing," said Tim Robbins, who's charity The Actors' Gang is supported by a grant from HFPA. 
While Christian Slater simply wasn't interested in the new category debate. 
"Look, I don't really think about it too much really. God bless them. They've got to try to figure it out and there's so many other things going on in the world right now that actually have value and meaning that I don't think about it," Slater said.
The other new changes were met with a mix of praise and grumbling, like the move to shrink the broadcast to three hours and remove some categories from the live telecast.
"Coming from a stage background, I just know how important all of that stuff is and how hard they work and I think that they deserve equal presentation," said Cynthia Erivo. "They earn their nomination just as much as everybody else has. So I don't know. I think that they deserve the same air time."
The HFPA, who puts on the Golden Globes, awards millions of dollars in grants to charities every year and celebrates their efforts work with an annual star-studded dinner. 
This year, one of the HFPA grants went to RAICES, an organization that helps families separated at the U.S. border. 
William H. Macy hosted the event. Amber Heard, Jennifer Garner and Charlize Theron were among the celebrity presenters.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp Has Had His Tattoo Of Amber Heard Removed
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp Has Had His Tattoo Of Amber Heard Removed:
http://www.ladbible.com/entertainment/film-and-tv-johnny-depp-has-had-his-tattoo-of-amber-heard-removed-20180623.

Thanks for watching, subscribe for more videos:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCm7bYPIzqusEcMk_1_tHqGg?sub_confirmation=1
 ¬†Johnny Depp might be one of the world's most famous men, but he's not immune to a bit of heartbreak.¬†The A-lister has enjoyed romances with Jennifer Grey, Sherilyn Fenn (aka Audrey off Twin Peaks), Winona Ryder, Kate Moss, Vanessa Paradis and, most recently, Amber Heard, to whom he was married until 2016.¬†Depp's body is something of a record of his turbulent private life, with various tattoos that speak to experiences and relationships that he has had over his now 30 plus year career. ¬†Now, in his first big interview since the split with Heard, he has revealed that he had a tattoo that referred to her removed from his body.Credit: PA¬†Where once it said 'Slim' across his fingers, it now reads 'Scum'. It isn't the first time he has had one changed - a previous tatt that read "Winona Forever", inked in honour of his ex Winona Rider, now reads 'Wino Forever'. Speaking to Rolling Stone, Depp opened up on how he felt during to protracted saga of his divorce from Amber Heard. ¬†"I was as low as I believe I could have gotten," he said. "The next step was, 'You're going to arrive somewhere with your eyes open and you're going to leave there with your eyes closed'. I couldn't take the pain every day."I poured myself a vodka in the morning and started writing until the tears filled my eyes and I couldn't see the page anymore."¬†"I kept trying to figure out what I'd done to deserve this. I'd tried being kind to everyone, helping everyone, being truthful to everyone. The truth is most important to me. And all this still happened."Credit: PA¬†Depp was accused of emotionally and physically abusing Heard throughout their relationship, something that he vehemently denies. ¬†On top of that, he is in reportedly deep trouble financially, having had his fortune - which was thought to be more than $600 million - reduced by divorce, legal wrangling and excessive spending. ¬†Depp has been cast in the new Fantastic Beasts movie, a move that has sparked outrage due to the allegations currently against him - allegations which, one suspects, it will take more than a tattoo artist to delete.  Featured Image Credit:   PA  
#JohnnyDeppHasHadHisTattooOfAmberHeardRemoved

snippet.title: Aquaman Movie Photo: Mera & Arthur Search For Clues
snippet.description: Jason Momoas Arthur and Amber Heards Mera search for clues in Atlantis in a new image from James Wans upcomingDC movie Aquaman . Fans recently got their first real look at the highly anticipated  Aquaman  movie when the first trailer  (finally) saw the light of day at last months San Diego Comic-Con. Among the other importanttidbits released about the movie from SDCC was Momoas revelation that Arthur Curry  wears denim pants in the poster , not leather as was originally thought. The trailer itself was of course filled with revelations of its own, includinga first look at the movies sprawling version of Atlantis, as well as hints about the  origins of Black Mantis . One other recent reveal from  Aquaman  director James Wan , that there will be no  Justice League  team  cameos in the movie, may come as something of a disappointment to some fans. Clearly, many DC fans are very excited about the movie as evidenced by all the  tweets about  Aquaman  during Comic-Con , not to mention  the cleverfan trailers  that have come out since the real trailer first dropped. Related: Aquaman Trailer Breakdown: 25 Secrets You Missed For Aquaman fans who just cant get enough glimpses of what the movie has in store,  EW  has exclusively released a new photo from the film that helps build the intrigue. In the image, Amber Heards Mera and Jason Momoas casually dressed Arthur Curry are seen in a chamber apparently inside a ruin within one of the Seven Kingdoms of Atlantis having a look at a very mysterious piece of technology. By the looks on their faces, theyre very happy to have stumbled across this particular object. See the photo below: Theres a definite Indiana Jones - specifically  Indiana Jones and the Kingdom of the Crystal Skull  - feel to the scene, with its stone walls, ancient-looking sculptures and the piece of technology itself, which Wan has revealed is actually a device used to play back an ancient recording. Mera and Arthur are here seeking clues as part of their quest to find the Trident of Neptune so they can use it in their battle against Aquamans half-brother King Orm (Patrick Wilson). It should be no surprise that theres a distinct Indiana Jones vibeto not only the plot but the above still, as Wan has revealed the Indiana Jones movies helped inspire his take on Aquaman. As the particular setting featured above is in fact located in Africa, the scene shown likely happens not long after the famous moment from the  Aquaman  trailer where Mera and Arthur both leap from a plane into the desert without parachutes (theyre also wearing the same costumes as in that scene from the trailer). Among the many mysteries the movie will have to clear up is how they both manage to survive their plane leap, sincetheres nothing but sand dunes underneath them. Source:  EW Tags: aquaman Looking for an  AD FREE EXPERIENCE  on ScreenRant?

More About Aquaman : Aquaman is a 2018 American superhero film based on the DC Comics character of the same name, distributed by Warner Bros. Pictures. It is the sixth installment in the DC Extended Universe (DCEU). Directed by James Wan, with a screenplay by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick and Will Beall, from a story by Geoff Johns, Wan and Beall, it stars Jason Momoa as the title character, with Amber Heard, Willem Dafoe, Patrick Wilson, Dolph Lundgren, Yahya Abdul-Mateen II, and Nicole Kidman in supporting roles. It is the third live-action theatrical film featuring the title character, following Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice (2016) and Justice League (2017) and the first full-length feature film centered around the character. In Aquaman, Arthur Curry, the heir to the underwater kingdom of Atlantis, must step forward to lead his people against his half-brother, Orm, who seeks to unite the seven underwater kingdoms against the surface world.

snippet.title: AMBER SWEENEY | STRONG ENOUGH COVER | SONG CRUSH SUNDAY
snippet.description:
SONG CRUSH SUNDAY WITH AMBER SWEENEY 

Strong Enough by Sheryl Crow

I picked this song for a couple reasons. The first being that I get to go see Sheryl Crow for my birthday this week, and I wanted to pay homage to a woman who has been teaching me all these years and didn‚Äôt know it. The first time I heard Sheryl Crow, my mind was blown. It was the first time I understood how powerful words could be, and how a really good song also told a really good story. This song tells such a sad, but real story. When I was younger, I remember wanting people to be in my life so bad, that I would rather they pretend to be something to me, than to be true to themselves and leave. I‚Äôm sure some of that came from unresolved abandonment issues. I learned the hard way that it‚Äôs better to live authentically than to pretend. Pretending can build resentment over time, and that resentment makes a deeper cut than the tear way back at the beginning would have been. That‚Äôs at least what this song means to me. 

I‚Äôm playing my trusty Breedlove acoustic, and we filmed this at my home studio in Southwest Washington. 

In honor of giving credit where credit is due, here is the songwriter information for ‚ÄúStrong Enough‚Äù: 

‚ÄúStrong Enough‚Äù written by -
Kevin Gilbert
Bill Bottrell
Sheryl Crow
Brian Macleod
David Baerwald
David Ricketts 

Thanks for watching and listening with your heart!

~Amber

snippet.title: London Fields | Official Trailer (2018) | Amber Heard | Film Threat Trailers
snippet.description:
Recently arrived in London in the hope of writing one last book before succumbing to a fatal illness, American author Samson Young (Billy Bob Thornton) falls in with a cast of characters who just might give him the story he is looking for. First, there is Keith Talent (Jim Sturgess) a small- time crook and dart player always on the lookout for his next scam. Then there‚Äôs Guy Clinch (Theo James), an upper class banker who hangs out at Ned‚Äôs favorite pub, searching for distraction from his boring life, his spoiled wife, and their monstrous toddler. And, just like a scene from a movie, into their lives walks Nicola Six (Amber Heard), a spectacularly beautiful woman-of-mystery who instantly ensnares all three men with her charms.  Of course, Ned and Keith want to possess her, but Sam sees something else‚Äîin Nicola he sees the heroine of the book he so desperately wants to write. Following her, studying her, and watching her become a different woman depending upon which man she is seducing, Sam starts weaving a tale, based on Nicola, or Nicola as he imagines her to be. He also discovers that the reason she lives like there‚Äôs no tomorrow, is that she‚Äôs fed up with her life and has secretly been plotting her own murder.  Now that Sam knows the climax of his story, the only question is who will the murderer be? Is it Keith, the criminal, Guy, the millionaire, or is it Sam himself‚Äîa dying man practicing a dying art, who will do anything to end his book‚Äîand his life‚Äîwith a big bang?

Based on the acclaimed international best-seller by Martin Amis, London Fields is a tantalizing, ultra-modern murder mystery about a murder that hasn‚Äôt taken place yet, a darkly comic vision of a world on the brink of collapse in which every character--and society itself--has a rendezvous with death. 

Directed by Mathew Cullen.

Starring Amber Heard, Billy Bob Thornton, Jim Sturgess, Theo James, Cara Delevingne.

snippet.title: Amber Heard wore a swimming cap to the 'Aquaman' premiere | Daily Celebrity News | Splash TV
snippet.description:
The 'Justice League' actress wowed fans in an emerald look from the autumn/winter '19/'19 collection of Pierpaolo Piccioli paired with gold Brian Atwood platform heels. 

SUBSCRIBE NOW : https://goo.gl/JaLP0U

Amber Heard wore a swimming cap to the 'Aquaman' premiere. 

The 32-year-old actress stepped onto the red carpet on in Leicester Square, wearing a Valentino haute couture green outfit with a matching swimming hat. 

The 'Justice League' actress wowed fans in an emerald look from the autumn/winter '19/'19 collection of Pierpaolo Piccioli paired with gold Brian Atwood platform heels. 

The stunning gown was emblazoned with green-and-gold-foil floral detailing and boasted a plunging neckline and trailing skirt with a thigh-high slit which the star paired with a simple gold bangle and a long neck chain. 

Although the blonde beauty channelled her fantasy alter ego for the red carpet, she admitted she constantly felt "uncomfortable" being submerged in water for the shoots and felt like she was "being hugged by baby angels" when she was allowed to wear a coat during breaks.

snippet.title: AQUAMAN Final Trailer (2018) | Jason Momoa, Amber Heard | In theaters December 21
snippet.description:
From Warner Bros. Pictures and director James Wan comes an action-packed adventure that spans the vast, visually breathtaking underwater world of the seven seas, ‚ÄúAquaman,‚Äù starring Jason Momoa in the title role.  The film reveals the origin story of half-human, half-Atlantean Arthur Curry and takes him on the journey of his lifetime‚Äîone that will not only force him to face who he really is, but to discover if he is worthy of who he was born to be‚Ä¶a king.

The film also stars Amber Heard (‚ÄúJustice League,‚Äù ‚ÄúMagic Mike XXL‚Äù) as Mera, a fierce warrior and Aquaman‚Äôs ally throughout his journey; Oscar nominee Willem Dafoe (‚ÄúPlatoon,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpider-Man 2‚Äù) as Vulko, council to the Atlantean throne; Patrick Wilson (‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù films, ‚ÄúWatchmen‚Äù) as Orm/Ocean Master, the present King of Atlantis; Dolph Lundgren (‚ÄúThe Expendables‚Äù films) as Nereus, King of the Atlantean tribe Xebel; Yahya Abdul-Mateen II (Netflix‚Äôs ‚ÄúThe Get Down‚Äù) as the vengeful Black Manta; and Oscar winner Nicole Kidman (‚ÄúThe Hours,‚Äù ‚ÄúLion‚Äù) as Arthur‚Äôs mom, Atlanna; as well as Ludi Lin (‚ÄúPower Rangers‚Äù) as Captain Murk, Atlantean Commando; and Temuera Morrison (‚ÄúStar Wars: Episode II ‚Äì Attack of the Clones,‚Äù ‚ÄúGreen Lantern‚Äù) as Arthur‚Äôs dad, Tom Curry.

Wan directs from a screenplay by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick (‚ÄúThe Conjuring 2‚Äù) and Will Beall (‚ÄúGangster Squad,‚Äù TV‚Äôs ‚ÄúTraining Day‚Äù), story by Geoff Johns & James Wan and Will Beall, based on characters from DC, Aquaman created by Paul Norris and Mort Weisinger.  The film is produced by Peter Safran and Rob Cowan, with Deborah Snyder, Zack Snyder, Jon Berg, Geoff Johns and Walter Hamada serving as executive producers.

Wan‚Äôs team behind the scenes includes such frequent collaborators as Oscar-nominated director of photography Don Burgess (‚ÄúThe Conjuring 2,‚Äù ‚ÄúForrest Gump‚Äù), his five-time editor Kirk Morri (‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù films, ‚ÄúFurious 7,‚Äù the ‚ÄúInsidious‚Äù films), and production designer Bill Brzeski (‚ÄúFurious 7‚Äù).  They are joined by costume designer Kym Barrett (‚ÄúThe Matrix‚Äù trilogy, ‚ÄúThe Amazing Spider-Man‚Äù) and composer Rupert Gregson-Williams (‚ÄúWonder Woman‚Äù).

Warner Bros. Pictures Presents a Safran Company Production, a James Wan Film, ‚ÄúAquaman.‚Äù  The film is set to hit theaters on December 21, 2018, in 3D and 2D and IMAX, and will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures, a Warner Bros. Entertainment Company.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp 'accuses Amber Heard of defecating in their marital bed'
snippet.description:
Amber Heard is accused of intentionally defecating in the marital bed she shared with Johnny Depp after a blazing row in the months leading up to their acrimonious separation and subsequent divorce.

Heard allegedly soiled the bed as a malicious prank after the Hollywood star arrived two-hours late for her 30th birthday party in April 2016, according to The Mirror.

Sources claim the warring couple‚Äôs housekeeper discovered excrement on the sheets after Depp, 55, stormed out of their Los Angeles penthouse following a heated row.

It‚Äôs understood that ‚Äòstrong photographic evidence‚Äô links Heard to the reported incident, while the actress has since claimed the fecal matter was left by their dog, Boo.

A source told The Mirror: 'Boo has some serious bowel control issues. There was never a joke, it wasn‚Äôt something done to be disrespectful.

'It was an innocent thing, it‚Äôs what pets will do. We don‚Äôt have anything else to say. Ms. Heard is moving on and we do not want to engage in this nonsense.'

The dogs, Pistol and Boo, were last in the news when Heard flew them into Australia on a private jet without putting them through quarantine in 2015.

Depp's ex-wife avoided jail time when she pleaded guilty to¬†falsifying border protection documents when when she imported the teacup Yorkshire terriers into Australia. Heard was handed a one-month good behavior bond and fined $1,000.

The couple also produced an apology video that was played in court, and later went viral. 'When you disrespect Australian law,' Depp deadpans in the video, 'they will tell you firmly'.

The incident sparked global headlines when Agriculture Minister and Deputy Prime Minister Barnaby Joyce said the dogs had better 'bugger off' back to the US or he'd arrange to have them put down.

It was alleged the pooches were not declared to customs officials on arrival.

The presence of the A-list canines was only discovered when their visit to a Gold Coast dog grooming salon was made public.¬†The dogs were quickly whisked out of the country before a 72-hour deadline lapsed when the canines would have to be seized.

Under strict Australian laws designed to keep disease at bay, dogs entering from the United States must be declared and have to spend 10 days in quarantine. Penalties for contravening the Quarantine Act range from fines to a maximum of 10 years in prison for the worst cases.

Depp was never charged over the incident.

Pistol was said to be a gift to Heard from her former girlfriend, artist Tasya van Ree, while Boo originally belonged to Depp.

He is believed to have wanted to keep custody of the pair, saying the dogs should not be split up but it was¬†Heard who was given custody of their beloved terriers.

Heard and Depp were married in 2015 but their relationship quickly unraveled.

A month after the bed defection incident, Heard that Depp ¬†grabbed her cellphone during an argument, 'wound up his arm like a baseball pitcher and threw the cell phone at me striking my cheek and eye with great force,' according to court filings.

But police officers found 'no evidence of any crime‚Äô, despite Heard appearing bruised in a picture she claims was taken after the alleged attack.

Heard later claimed in court papers : 'Johnny has a long-held and widely acknowledged public and private history of drug and alcohol abuse. He has a short fuse.'

In legal papers submitted during the couple's divorce in 2017, Heard claimed he made ‚Äúparanoid and irrational accusations about some delusional idea‚Äù.

'He began obsessing about something untrue and his demeanour changed dramatically. He became angry,' she wrote.

The actor is attempting to clear his name with a High Court case in London against a British newspaper that reported Heard's allegations earlier this year.

In court papers seen by the Mail On Sunday, Depp's legal team denies absolutely that the star assaulted his former wife.

'The phone did not hit Ms Heard on the face or elsewhere,' say his lawyers. 'Nor did [Depp] pull Ms Heard's hair or strike her, or grab her face or touch her.'

The High Court papers cite depositions from two Los Angeles police officers, who appear to contradict Ms Heard's version of events.

They say they arrived at the couple's home 25 minutes after the alleged attack, yet saw no damage to the property, adding that a crying Heard told them she wasn't hurt and did not need medical attention. Nor did they see injuries or swellings on her face.

His lawyers claim he brought two of his security team along with him because he 'was concerned' about what Ms Heard would do.

They too appear to contradict her version of events, claiming that Depp was not in fact physically close to his wife during the incident.

MailOnline has contacted a representative for further comment.

snippet.title: Diane Abbott calls on Amber Rudd to resign over Windrush - Daily Mail
snippet.description:
The Home Secretary said that 'unfortunately' she was not aware of the policy - introduced when Theresa May was in charge of the department - and will be looking at it again. Her shocking admission came after it emerged last night that officials have been using targets for the voluntary removal of illegal immigrants since 2014. Ms Rudd was first challenged about the targets yesterday in front of the Home Affairs Select Committee - but said she had never heard of them. And this morning she was hauled back to the House of Commons (pictured) to explain her handling of the Windrush scandal. She faced repeated calls to resign over the debacle by Labour MPs - but insisted she is the right person to 'put things right'. Despite the latest debacle over Windrush, the Prime Minister's spokesman said she still has 'full confidence' in Ms Rudd.

snippet.title: Amber Heard denies report that Johnny Depp accused her of defecating in their marital bed
snippet.description:
Amber Heard denies report that Johnny Depp accused her of defecating in their marital bed
Johnny Depp has accused former wife Amber Heard of deliberately soiling their marital bed in revenge for turning up two hours late to her 30th birthday bash.
The troubled actor claims the incident sparked the violent argument that led to the breakdown of their marriage.
Depp had stormed out of the couple‚Äôs Los Angeles penthouse after discovering the pile of poo between the sheets after Heard‚Äôs party in April 2016, a friend of the "Pirates of the Caribbean" star told The Mirror.
Heard blamed the deposit on her dog Boo, who has bowel problems, but a housekeeper who had to clean up the mess the following day suggested the droppings were too large to have come from the little pooch.
Depp, 55, believes there is ‚Äústrong, photographic evidence that connected Amber to the feces‚Äù and it was left as a ‚Äúprank," the friend said.
But a representative for the actress denied any malicious intent, insisting it was an unfortunate accident.
‚ÄúBoo has some serious bowel control issues. There was never a joke, it wasn‚Äôt something done to be disrespectful,‚Äù the rep told the Mirror.
‚ÄúIt was an innocent thing, it‚Äôs what pets will do. We don‚Äôt have anything else to say. Ms. Heard is moving on and we do not want to engage in this nonsense.‚Äù
In May 2016, a month later, the couple had another argument about the poo which turned violent and culminated in Depp allegedly hurling Heard‚Äôs mobile phone, hitting her in the face.

snippet.title: Live Your Purpose (and get paid for it) with Amber Valdez
snippet.description:
Amber Valdez is a former TV Personality and NFL Cheerleader turned Life Purpose Cheerleader, who is leading 1 million+ individuals to love themselves, own their worth so they can live their purpose and GET PAID to change the world. 

She is the creator of #StickieAffirmations, the Team Live Your Purpose Movement, The Worthy Goddess Workshop, The Let Your Light Shine LIVE & Turn You're Crazy Into Your Purpose online bootcamps, and the author of "Stickie Affirmations to Live Your Purpose" that went #1 on the Amazon's Best-Seller list. 

Amber serves as a life purpose coach, online bootcamp facilitator, International speaker and live stream queen! Amber creates deep trust and respect through her down to earth, real personality, no bull shit, spunky yet vulnerable coaching style that allows her students to feel, seen, heard, accepted and loved.  

Amber is committed to being the cheerleader she never had by reminding Light Workers from around the world that they matter, they are worthy and their purpose matters.

In this episode Amber shares:
- Her personal struggles growing up in an abusive home
- Seeking validation and a sense of self in the wrong places
- Healing from the past, re-writing the future and becoming her own cheerleader
- The essential key to creating a real impact online (that most people are missing)
- How to find your light, share your voice and start living your purpose
- Why the world needs lightworkers now more than ever
- How to get out of your own way and step into your greatness
- Why support and a cheer squad of high vibing soul sisters is essential to your growth
- Why its completely possible (and encouraged) to make money while living your purpose and making a difference

snippet.title: LONDON FIELDS MOVIE TRAILER OFFICIAL 2018 Amber Heard Thriller Mystery Movie YouTube
snippet.description:
In the movie London Fields, (which is based on the NY Times best selling novel of the same name by Martin Amis), clairvoyant femme fatale, Nicola Six (Amber Heard), has been living with a dark premonition of her impending death by murder.

She begins a tangled love affair with three uniquely different men: one of whom she knows will be her murderer.

Cara Delevingne, Jason Isaacs, Billy Bob Thornton, Theo James, Jim Sturgess and Jaimie Alexander co-star in the movie London Fields.

Director of the film, Martin Cullen, has only worked behind the camera on music videos. This is his first movie. He may be best known for directing the Adele music video, Chasing Pavements and the Katy Perry music video California Gurls.

Share this video:
https://youtu.be/eBGF4aLbcT4

snippet.title: Amber Heard | Change from Childhood to 32 Years Old
snippet.description:
Amber Laura Heard (born April 22, 1986) is an American actress. She made her film debut in 2004 in the sports drama Friday Night Lights. After small roles in North Country and Alpha Dog, Heard played her first leading role in All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006) and appeared in The CW television show Hidden Palms (2007).
Heard's breakthrough came in 2008 with roles in Never Back Down and Pineapple Express. She received the Breakthrough Award at Young Hollywood Awards. Her appearance in films such as The Informers, The Stepfather, Zombieland, and The Joneses brought her further attention. She next starred in John Carpenter's The Ward, alongside Nicolas Cage in Drive Angry, and alongside Johnny Depp in The Rum Diary, for which she won a Spotlight Award at the Hollywood Film Festival. In 2014 she appeared in 3 Days to Kill, and in 2015 in Magic Mike XXL and The Danish Girl. She played Mera in the 2017 superhero film Justice League, a role she will reprise in the 2018 film Aquaman. #AmberHeard

Music:

snippet.title: Aquaman (2018) | Official Trailer Final# Jason Momoa, Amber Heard, Nicole Kidman
snippet.description:
SYNOPSIS:
Arthur Curry learns that he is the heir to the underwater kingdom of Atlantis, and must step forward to lead his people and be a hero to the world.

From Warner Bros. Pictures and director James Wan comes an action-packed adventure that spans the vast, visually breathtaking underwater world of the seven seas, Aquaman, starring Jason Momoa in the title role. The film reveals the origin story of half-human, half-Atlantean Arthur Curry and takes him on the journey of his lifetime‚Äîone that will not only force him to face who he really is, but to discover if he is worthy of who he was born to be‚Ä¶a king.

The film also stars Amber Heard (Justice League, Magic Mike XXL) as Mera, a fierce warrior and Aquaman‚Äôs ally throughout his journey; Oscar nominee Willem Dafoe (Platoon, Spider-Man 2) as Vulko, council to the Atlantean throne; Patrick Wilson (The Conjuring films, Watchmen) as Orm/Ocean Master, the present King of Atlantis; Dolph Lundgren (The Expendables films), King of the Atlantean tribe Xebel; Yahya Abdul-Mateen II (upcoming Baywatch, Netflix‚Äôs The Get Down) as the vengeful Black Manta; and Oscar winner Nicole Kidman (The Hours, Lion) as Arthur‚Äôs mom, Atlanna; as well as Ludi Lin (Power Rangers) as Captain Murk, Atlantean Commando; and Temuera Morrison (Star Wars: Episode II ‚Äì Attack of the Clones, Green Lantern) as Arthur‚Äôs dad, Tom Curry.

Wan directs from a screenplay by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick (The Conjuring 2) and Will Beall (Gangster Squad, TV‚Äôs Training Day), story by Geoff Johns & James Wan and Will Beall, based on characters from DC, Aquaman created by Paul Norris and Mort Weisinger. The film is produced by Peter Safran and Rob Cowan, with Deborah Snyder, Zack Snyder, Jon Berg, Geoff Johns and Walter Hamada serving as executive producers.

Wan‚Äôs team behind the scenes includes such frequent collaborators as Oscar-nominated director of photography Don Burgess (The Conjuring 2, Forrest Gump), his five-time editor Kirk Morri (The Conjuring films, Furious 7, the Insidious films), and production designer Bill Brzeski (Furious 7). They are joined by costume designer Kym Barrett (The Matrix trilogy, The Amazing Spider-Man) and composer Rupert Gregson-Williams (Wonder Woman).

Warner Bros. Pictures Presents a Safran Company Production, a James Waan Film, Aquaman. The film is set to hit theaters on December 21, 2018 in 3D and 2D and IMAX, and will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures, a Warner Bros. Entertainment Company.

snippet.title: Aquaman   Official Trailer 1/Jason Momoa,Amber Heard/James Wan/14Dec18
snippet.description:
From Warner Bros. Pictures and director James Wan comes an action-packed adventure that spans the vast, visually breathtaking underwater world of the seven seas, ‚ÄúAquaman,‚Äù starring Jason Momoa in the title role.  The film reveals the origin story of half-human, half-Atlantean Arthur Curry and takes him on the journey of his lifetime‚Äîone that will not only force him to face who he really is, but to discover if he is worthy of who he was born to be‚Ä¶a king.

The film also stars Amber Heard (‚ÄúJustice League,‚Äù ‚ÄúMagic Mike XXL‚Äù) as Mera, a fierce warrior and Aquaman‚Äôs ally throughout his journey; Oscar nominee Willem Dafoe (‚ÄúPlatoon,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpider-Man 2‚Äù) as Vulko, council to the Atlantean throne; Patrick Wilson (‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù films, ‚ÄúWatchmen‚Äù) as Orm/Ocean Master, the present King of Atlantis; Dolph Lundgren (‚ÄúThe Expendables‚Äù films) as Nereus, King of the Atlantean tribe Xebel; Yahya Abdul-Mateen II (Netflix‚Äôs ‚ÄúThe Get Down‚Äù) as the vengeful Black Manta; and Oscar winner Nicole Kidman (‚ÄúThe Hours,‚Äù ‚ÄúLion‚Äù) as Arthur‚Äôs mom, Atlanna; as well as Ludi Lin (‚ÄúPower Rangers‚Äù) as Captain Murk, Atlantean Commando; and Temuera Morrison (‚ÄúStar Wars: Episode II ‚Äì Attack of the Clones,‚Äù ‚ÄúGreen Lantern‚Äù) as Arthur‚Äôs dad, Tom Curry.

Wan directs from a screenplay by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick (‚ÄúThe Conjuring 2‚Äù) and Will Beall (‚ÄúGangster Squad,‚Äù TV‚Äôs ‚ÄúTraining Day‚Äù), story by Geoff Johns & James Wan and Will Beall, based on characters from DC, Aquaman created by Paul Norris and Mort Weisinger.  The film is produced by Peter Safran and Rob Cowan, with Deborah Snyder, Zack Snyder, Jon Berg, Geoff Johns and Walter Hamada serving as executive producers.

Wan‚Äôs team behind the scenes includes such frequent collaborators as Oscar-nominated director of photography Don Burgess (‚ÄúThe Conjuring 2,‚Äù ‚ÄúForrest Gump‚Äù), his five-time editor Kirk Morri (‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù films, ‚ÄúFurious 7,‚Äù the ‚ÄúInsidious‚Äù films), and production designer Bill Brzeski (‚ÄúFurious 7‚Äù).  They are joined by costume designer Kym Barrett (‚ÄúThe Matrix‚Äù trilogy, ‚ÄúThe Amazing Spider-Man‚Äù) and composer Rupert Gregson-Williams (‚ÄúWonder Woman‚Äù).

Warner Bros. Pictures Presents a Safran Company Production, a James Wan Film, ‚ÄúAquaman.‚Äù  The film is set to hit theaters on December 21, 2018, in 3D and 2D and IMAX, and will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures, a Warner Bros. Entertainment Company.

snippet.title: Amber Heard promo for Aquaman.
snippet.description:
Amber Heard promo for Aquaman.

Actor Amber Heard looked back at the time when she raised her voice about the physical and emotional abuse she allegedly suffered at the hands of her former husband and actor Johnny Depp.

Female stars from Hollywood came together to commemorate a year since the #MeToo movement that shook the entertainment industry at the Incredible Women gala hosted by Porter Magazine on Tuesday, reports variety.com.

Heard read aloud from an open letter she had written for the publication in December of 2016, shortly after filing for divorce from Depp.
Amber Heard arrives at the world premiere of Her Smell at the Toronto International Film Festival (TIFF) in Toronto. (REUTERS)

She alleged that the actor had physically and emotionally abused her, which Depp denied. She donated her entire divorce settlement to domestic violence and children's charities.

Before reading the letter, she told the crowd that she wrote it to her "silent sisters" because "at the time, my voice was alone, it was one that certainly felt alone".

"And Porter Magazine ran this open letter when it was perhaps most difficult, and for that reason I feel honoured to be here sharing this space with so many brave, powerful women, and I just wanted to take a moment to say how much I appreciate it. Also, crazy how relevant these words are today, two and a half years later," she added.

Heard was one of several women who took their heels off while performing on stage, as a statement of solidarity.

snippet.title: Amber Heard discusses her recent trip to Jordan, helping Syrian refugees, calls it life changing
snippet.description:
(25 Apr 2018) AMBER HEARD DISCUSSES HER RECENT TRIP TO JORDAN, HELPING SYRIAN REFUGEES, CALLS IT LIFE CHANGING
Actress Amber Heard has described the "unimaginable" conditions endured by Syrian refugees and those affected by the country's civil war.
Heard recently spent a spent a week in Jordan as part of a delegation of the Syrian American Medical Society (SAMS), visiting the kingdom's largest camp for Syrian refugees and rehabilitation centers for those wounded in Syria's seven-year-old civil war.
Speaking at CinemaCon in Las Vegas Tuesday (24 APRIL 2018) while promoting upcoming DC superhero movie "Aquaman," the actress explained how she first got involved with the Syrian aid effort.
"I have an amazing group of Syrian friends and as the family and friends, as more and more people come over from Syria and are affected by the crisis, I was once at a dinner at my adopted Syrian family's house and I said, you know, 'I'm just hearing and more of these stories and how can I help?'" 
"I was lucky enough to have sat next to someone who had an answer and he said, 'My friend's uncle is a doctor and he said I work with this organization called the Syrian American Medical Society - SAMS for short. And it's not political it's not like, you know, there's no like creed or anthem and it was like no agenda. It's just simply to bring medical care to some of the most vulnerable people in the world which are the people that are affected by the Syrian crisis.'" 
In early April, Heard joined SAMS's 53-member medical mission to Jordan, home to about 660,000 of some 5.5 million Syrian refugees. Most of the displaced Syrians have settled in overburdened regional host countries, struggling to survive on menial jobs, food vouchers and small cash stipends from aid groups.
Over the week, the medical mission visited Zaatari, Jordan's largest camp for Syrian refugees, as well as rehabilitation centers for the wounded.
"The Zaatari camp, which is the one I visited, is the largest for the Syrian refugees in the world and over half, well over half the population at the camp, are children," said Heard. "How could you not be affected? ‚Ä¶ I wanted to be there on the ground and wanted to bring as much attention and awareness as I possibly could." 
The actress added that she was touched by "the light and the spirit and the joy and the generosity and the warmth in the eyes of every person I met at that camp."
"I look at the gift of my life and that around us and I will continue to work tirelessly for not just people like that, but organizations that help people like that because that's key. You know? You can't fight for yourself. You need someone to do it for you."

snippet.title: Amber Heard holds hands with Heidi Klum's ex Vito Schnabel in NYC - 247 News
snippet.description: Amber Heard and Vito Schnabel were first spotted together in the back seat of a dark SUV in New York City¬†in early May.And it looks as if the spark has just gotten stronger between the budding lovebirds.On Tuesday the 32-year-old actress from Texas and the 31-year-old Brooklyn-born art curator look to be going strong as they were pictured holding hands while walking in New York City.Vito was puffing away on a cigarette as he smiled, clearly relishing his time with the ex-wife of Johnny Depp.He had on a white shirt and slacks with blue sneakers and wore a pair of yellow-tinted mirrored sunglasses.Heard was all dolled up for her date with the art guru with pretty makeup and her hair brushed back.The Justice League actress wore a very thin white T-shirt that left little to the imagination with an unusual thin-strapped dress over it.There was also a large hole on her left side that exposed her nude-toned bra.The blonde beauty - who can next be seen in Aquaman - added black pointed boots that showed off her long, toned legs.She also had marks on her legs from her tight socks she must have worn earlier.A long black-and-gold shoulder purse by YSL added pizzazz as did a silver chain necklace and stylish earrings.And the star -¬†who made her film debut in the 2004 sports drama Friday Night Lights with Billy Bob Thornton - added several silver rings on her left hand.The couple looked in sync as they walked past an outdoor restaurant as fans took a gander.Later they crossed a street and walked to a parking area where the 3 Days To Kill actress opened her purse to pay a fee.Later the lovebirds got very close as they enjoyed a very long dinner at Italian restaurant Bar Pitti on Sixth Avenue.They had on the same clothes and appeared to be in a riveting conversation over a bottle of red wine and some Italian sparkling water.Vito was no doubt charming his lady love with all his knowledge of the art world.In early May, they were caught by surprise as they seemed to be deep in conversation in a car.Heard was last linked to Tesla founder Elon Musk and Schnabel broke off his romance with supermodel Heidi Klum last year.Amber wore her flaxen locks down and had on a casual white T-shirt as she appeared a bit sleepy while looking out her opened window.Vito wore his sunglasses down on his nose and was slouched down in his car seat as he had an intense expression on his face.The pairing is unusual because they have never been seen together before and no one knew they were friends.Also, while Amber lives in Los Angeles, Vito calls New York City home.Heard was last linked to Musk, who she was on and off with from 2016 until 2017.Musk is now dating musical artist Grimes and they made their public debut as a couple the Met Gala, where Heard was also a guest.Heard was previously married to Depp from 2015 until 2016.They had an ugly and very public split that included accusations of physical and mental abuse.Schnabel dated America's Got Talent star Klum, 44, off and on from 201

snippet.title: Amber Heard flashes her flat stomach in crop top and sweats while taking a break from filming
snippet.description: Earlier this month, she was reportedly spotted on a 'flirty' date with Sean Penn.And on Monday, Amber Heard was seen on the set of her movie Run Away With Me in Los Angeles.The 31-year-old actress flaunted her flat stomach in her sweats and crop top ensemble.Amber was seen taking a break from filming to take a call.The Texas-born beauty chose cuffed gray sweat bottoms, which she paired with a black criss-cross strapped tank top.Amber, who showed off her flat midsection, donned a hot pink patterned bra and a plaid cover up.The screen star finished off her character's ensemble with bold slides, a studded cross body handbag and a fake rose tattoo on her upper chest.The actress styled her long blonde locks loose in waves; she sported a touch of red dye on the tips of her hair.Amber, who wore large gold hoop earrings, painted her pout a pink hue with a touch of shadow on her lids; her nails were painted red with two gold accent nails.The film Run Away With Me is about an American who falls for a model in Paris; the duo then become involved in the criminal modeling world.According to Page Six, Amber was seen enjoying dinner with Sean Penn earlier this month.They were seen at Tower Bar at the Sunset Tower looking 'flirty and intimate with each other.' She previously dated billionaire Elon Musk and was married to Johnny Depp from February 2015 until splitting in May 2016.

snippet.title: Funny Pakistani Independent candidate Amber Shahzada campaign in Lahore
snippet.description:
It‚Äôs a general rule among politicians that whenever they campaign for an election, they promise to weed out corruption. Whether they believe in it or not is a different problem but they do so for some simple reasons. First, the working class doesn‚Äôt like it. Second, it hampers the system. And finally, because it‚Äôs unlawful. However, have you ever heard of a Prime Ministerial candidate who promises to promote corruption if he wins?
It‚Äôs a general rule among politicians that whenever they campaign for an election, they promise to weed out corruption. Whether they believe in it or not is a different problem but they do so for some simple reasons. First, the working class doesn‚Äôt like it. Second, it hampers the system. And finally, because it‚Äôs unlawful. However, have you ever heard of a Prime Ministerial candidate who promises to promote corruption if he wins?

His party has different agenda from all other parties which believes in slashing defence budget, improving tax system, making judiciary, police and Election Commission of Pakistan free from political influence and interference, fair accountability with special focus on eradication of corruption. Mega projects in health and education sectors are also his party agenda, the chairman says.
Amber Shahzada is the candidate who knows the art of contesting election with ‚Äòsmall amount of money‚Äô which he says is sponsored by his friends and fans on every election, and strongly condemns the purchased-victory and votes. However, he does not know how much expenses incur on his election every year.
I think that politicians could be corrupt, but only as required and not as they wish. If my government comes into power, I will minimise corruption and legalise it. If someone less corrupt comes into power, the country will progress.‚Äù
Shahzada always wears a Turkish-style hat, and sports a handlebar moustache, and is very active on his twitter account. He has announced his plans to contest for NA-125, a constituency for the National Assembly of Pakistan in Lahore. He is up against the major political parties in Pakistan and Maryam Nawaz, former prime minister Nawaz Sharif‚Äôs daughter, who will contest as an independent candidate.

‚ÄúIt is my firm belief that I‚Äôll be victorious when Election Commission will be completely impartial, when the census will be held truly on real grounds, and police will stop interference into political system,‚Äù Shehzada speaks, making specific gesture with both his hands

By: Faisal Anjum Satti

snippet.title: Amber Heard 'Why Be a Human Rights Activist?' | Hague Talks
snippet.description:
IMAGINE THE WORLD WE WANT
There are dreamers and there are realists in this world. You would think the dreamers would find the dreamers and the realists would find the realists but‚Ä¶ more often than not, the opposite is true. You see the dreamers need the realists to keep them from soaring too close to the sun. And the realists‚Ä¶ well, without the dreamers, they might not ever get off the ground.‚Äù ‚Äî Modern Family

This Hague Talks will bring all of you dreamers and the realists together ‚Äì because we know we need you both!

ABOUT THE SPEAKER
Amber Heard is a world-renowned actress and an outspoken advocate for Women‚Äôs and Children‚Äôs rights. She devotes her time off-screen to organizations like ACLU and Art of Elysium, and most recently returned from a humanitarian trip to Jordan to visit Syrian refugees with the Syrian American Medical Society (SAMS). Amber is a Human Rights Champion of the UN Human Rights Officeand an Ambassador for ACLU for Violence Against Women, lending her voice and support to promote the principles of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights.

On the occasion of the 70thanniversary of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights, Hollywood actress Amber Heard will share her captivating story and discuss her perspective on gender equality, LGBTI rights and much more.

Twitter: @realamberheard
Facebook: AmberHeardOfficial/
#standup4humanrights
@UNhumanrights
@unitednationshumanrights

HAGUE TALKS is a meeting place for creative minds, peace inventors and game changers in the field of peace and justice.
For more info visit www.haguetalks.com

Amber Laura Heard (born April 22, 1986) is an American actress. She made her film debut in 2004 in the sports drama Friday Night Lights. After small roles in North Country and Alpha Dog, Heard played her first leading role in All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006) and appeared in The CW television show Hidden Palms (2007).

Heard's breakthrough came in 2008 with roles in Never Back Down and Pineapple Express. She received the Breakthrough Award at Young Hollywood Awards. Her appearance in films such as The Informers, The Stepfather, Zombieland, and The Joneses brought her further attention. She next starred in John Carpenter's The Ward, alongside Nicolas Cage in Drive Angry, and alongside Johnny Depp in The Rum Diary, for which she won a Spotlight Award at the Hollywood Film Festival. In 2014 she appeared in 3 Days to Kill, and in 2015 in Magic Mike XXL and The Danish Girl. She played Mera in the 2017 superhero film Justice League, which she reprised in Aquaman.
